4
00:01:11,167 --> 00:01:14,292
[Vintage Malayalam song playing]

5
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,500
[Musical Night
by Cochin Kalamela]

6
00:01:58,918 --> 00:02:00,584
- Hey, son... Psst!
- Huh?

7
00:02:00,834 --> 00:02:02,125
Here's the orchestra list.

8
00:02:02,709 --> 00:02:03,959
This is the final song.

9
00:02:04,042 --> 00:02:06,209
Don't forget to add my name
at the end of the announcement.

10
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:07,918
Saji Pattambi, Troupe Manager.
Got it?

11
00:02:07,959 --> 00:02:09,167
- What was that?
- Saji Pattambi!

12
00:02:09,209 --> 00:02:10,626
- Right, right.
- Okay.

13
00:02:10,959 --> 00:02:12,959
[song continues]

14
00:02:20,417 --> 00:02:21,584
- Hey, Razak...
- Yeah?

15
00:02:21,626 --> 00:02:22,918
The visas for the Europe trip arrived.

16
00:02:24,083 --> 00:02:26,125
Good for you, Saji Chetta.

17
00:02:27,209 --> 00:02:28,417
Oh no!

18
00:02:29,209 --> 00:02:30,250
What's wrong?

19
00:02:30,751 --> 00:02:33,083
We submitted 15 passports
for the trip.

20
00:02:33,375 --> 00:02:35,292
But we got visas
for only 14 people.

21
00:02:35,584 --> 00:02:36,751
One person's visa is missing.

22
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,167
Whose visa is it?

23
00:02:50,959 --> 00:02:53,292
Keyboard: Francis.

24
00:02:54,626 --> 00:02:55,918
Francis Chettan is cleared.

25
00:02:55,959 --> 00:02:58,542
Violin: Xavier,

26
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,334
Linto,

27
00:03:00,542 --> 00:03:01,959
Kundara Das.

28
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,542
The entire violin team
has received visas.

29
00:03:03,834 --> 00:03:06,209
Tumba: Joy.

30
00:03:07,542 --> 00:03:08,500
Tumba Joy made it too.

31
00:03:08,542 --> 00:03:12,334
Tabla: Surendran, Chacko.

32
00:03:14,083 --> 00:03:15,751
Even Chacko, the troublemaker,
got through.

33
00:03:15,792 --> 00:03:18,584
Prabhendu on electric guitar.

34
00:03:33,751 --> 00:03:34,959
- Hey, Razak...
- Yeah?

35
00:03:35,292 --> 00:03:36,918
It's Prabhendu who didn't
get the visa.

36
00:04:14,959 --> 00:04:16,334
- And then?
- Huh?!

37
00:04:16,751 --> 00:04:17,834
Okay, okay.

38
00:04:18,751 --> 00:04:20,083
Let me sleep for a bit.

39
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:24,500
Prabha...

40
00:04:24,792 --> 00:04:25,834
What's going on?

41
00:04:25,959 --> 00:04:28,250
I'm searching for a jacket
to handle the cold in Europe.

42
00:04:28,834 --> 00:04:31,542
My jacket from the US tour
has turned all mouldy.

43
00:04:32,167 --> 00:04:34,709
I have to place the order today
to get it before we leave.

44
00:04:34,751 --> 00:04:36,083
Ah, true, true.

45
00:04:36,334 --> 00:04:39,125
Hey, that room behind
our rehearsal space...

46
00:04:39,167 --> 00:04:40,876
I'm going to use it
for two months, okay?

47
00:04:40,918 --> 00:04:42,250
I'm vacating my current apartment.

48
00:04:42,292 --> 00:04:44,083
So, to store my stuff...

49
00:04:44,292 --> 00:04:45,584
So you already vacated your flat?

50
00:04:45,626 --> 00:04:47,626
What is this? You could've
at least asked me first!

51
00:04:47,751 --> 00:04:49,792
Just a second.
Let me just enter this OTP.

52
00:04:49,834 --> 00:04:51,751
- Wait, wait! Don't enter it!
- 4--

53
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,334
They've cut the electric guitar, man.

54
00:04:53,375 --> 00:04:55,125
You're the only one
who's not coming on the trip!

55
00:04:55,417 --> 00:04:56,417
What?!

56
00:04:58,125 --> 00:04:59,209
And then?

57
00:05:03,167 --> 00:05:05,083
- Who's having the omelette?
- Just keep it here.

58
00:05:05,375 --> 00:05:06,626
How about some
chicken fry for you, sir?

59
00:05:06,667 --> 00:05:07,667
It's our speciality.

60
00:05:08,417 --> 00:05:09,417
We've also got quail fry.

61
00:05:09,918 --> 00:05:11,542
- No need.
- We have pork with Chinese potatoes.

62
00:05:11,667 --> 00:05:13,292
- It's amazing.
- Get going, will you?

63
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:15,083
He's a Namboothiri (Brahmin).
Pure veg.

64
00:05:15,584 --> 00:05:17,334
Then I'll remove the pork
and get him the Chinese potatoes.

65
00:05:17,375 --> 00:05:19,918
Hey, this isn't some wedding spread
where food keeps coming.

66
00:05:19,959 --> 00:05:21,083
I still have to pay you, right?

67
00:05:23,751 --> 00:05:25,792
Will this idiot go around
asking everyone the same thing?

68
00:05:26,667 --> 00:05:28,834
We don't even have enough budget
for everyone's omelettes.

69
00:05:29,209 --> 00:05:30,709
If budget was a problem,
you should've said it earlier.

70
00:05:30,751 --> 00:05:34,417
You know, adding an omelette to
the dosa gives it a touch of luxury.

71
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:36,500
I mean the electric guitar here,
not the omelette!

72
00:05:36,542 --> 00:05:38,876
Yeah, I asked them
the exact same thing.

73
00:05:39,167 --> 00:05:41,250
Then, that sponsor guy
sent a message.

74
00:05:41,292 --> 00:05:42,292
Let me find it.

75
00:05:43,709 --> 00:05:46,042
Chetta, one of the investors
pulled out at the last minute.

76
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:47,709
We can pull through only
if we remove one person.

77
00:05:47,834 --> 00:05:48,918
- So I...
- And also...

78
00:05:48,959 --> 00:05:51,125
Please convey my special apologies
to Prabhendu Ma'am.

79
00:05:51,834 --> 00:05:53,083
Prabhendu "Ma'am"?
Idiot!

80
00:05:54,125 --> 00:05:55,125
Look, Prabha...

81
00:05:55,584 --> 00:05:57,292
Don't think I'm just trying
to make you feel better.

82
00:05:57,959 --> 00:05:59,459
What if this is actually
for the best?

83
00:05:59,667 --> 00:06:03,000
What? Being broke,
homeless for two months, and starving?!

84
00:06:03,042 --> 00:06:04,209
Oh, give me a break!

85
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:06,083
It's not like you come from
some poor household!

86
00:06:06,459 --> 00:06:10,626
Wouldn't even a tiny bit of
your dad's and brother's puja income

87
00:06:10,667 --> 00:06:13,042
be enough for you
to manage a full Europe tour?

88
00:06:13,167 --> 00:06:15,125
Wasn't it your ego that made you
snap your sacred thread

89
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:16,751
and choose to live by cutting costs?

90
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:19,334
If someone loses faith
and becomes an atheist,

91
00:06:19,375 --> 00:06:20,792
that's their personal choice.

92
00:06:21,209 --> 00:06:23,667
That is not ego.
That's confidence.

93
00:06:24,167 --> 00:06:26,626
- No, Prabha... I didn't mean--
- I'm not finished.

94
00:06:26,834 --> 00:06:28,626
To become a truly
passionate musician,

95
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:30,417
you have to sacrifice
a lot of things.

96
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,626
Just imagine if A.R. Rahman
had played it safe,

97
00:06:32,667 --> 00:06:34,792
packed his lunch every day
and gone to a bank job,

98
00:06:34,834 --> 00:06:37,375
would we have even half the songs
we performed on stage today?

99
00:06:37,751 --> 00:06:40,042
Prabha, I wasn't trying
to argue with you.

100
00:06:40,542 --> 00:06:43,626
What I actually wanted to talk about
was the passion you have.

101
00:06:44,876 --> 00:06:47,667
You're the most talented person
in our troupe.

102
00:06:47,959 --> 00:06:50,042
Have any of these guys
ever played for a movie?

103
00:06:50,167 --> 00:06:53,209
You're the only one they call
for studio recordings, right?

104
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:56,000
But that only happens
once in a while, right?

105
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:58,083
Anyway, since your trip is cancelled,

106
00:06:58,167 --> 00:07:00,459
you should attend your father's
70th birthday celebration.

107
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:02,375
Your elder brother called you
so many times, right?

108
00:07:02,542 --> 00:07:03,709
No, that's not a good idea.

109
00:07:03,751 --> 00:07:04,751
Look...

110
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:07,959
There's a proven trend of grumpy dads
becoming warm and loving

111
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,792
once they hit 70.

112
00:07:10,209 --> 00:07:12,209
This is your chance to slip in
and stay there for some time.

113
00:07:12,542 --> 00:07:15,042
You can save money
on food and rent, right?

114
00:07:15,459 --> 00:07:17,792
Plus, free WiFi, free laundry!
How great is that?

115
00:07:17,834 --> 00:07:19,292
Hey, son!
Got any quail eggs?

116
00:07:19,334 --> 00:07:20,584
Him and his damn eggs!

117
00:07:20,709 --> 00:07:22,500
Eggs! Eggs! Eggs!

118
00:07:22,542 --> 00:07:24,250
Where do you keep
shoving all these eggs?

119
00:07:24,417 --> 00:07:26,167
So now it's quail eggs
instead of chicken eggs?

120
00:07:26,209 --> 00:07:27,584
Can't you eat a meal
without eggs, huh?

121
00:07:27,626 --> 00:07:30,209
[Radiant at 70
- Neelakandan Namboothiri]

122
00:07:35,584 --> 00:07:36,584
Indu...

123
00:07:36,918 --> 00:07:38,209
I know you won't come.

124
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,667
But still, whenever you're
free, if you come home,

125
00:07:40,709 --> 00:07:42,959
it would make Dad very happy,

126
00:07:43,667 --> 00:07:45,292
even if he doesn't express it.

127
00:07:46,083 --> 00:07:48,500
Even uncle keeps talking
about wanting to see you.

128
00:07:56,792 --> 00:07:57,959
I'm busy.

129
00:07:58,417 --> 00:07:59,459
I'll try.

130
00:08:19,042 --> 00:08:21,292
Passengers getting down at this stop,
please step out.

131
00:08:28,417 --> 00:08:30,334
[Radiant at 70
- Neelakandan Namboothiri]

132
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:31,500
Hello...

133
00:08:31,834 --> 00:08:32,834
Huh?

134
00:08:32,876 --> 00:08:34,334
Aadi, no.
You'll get hurt.

135
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:36,250
When was this?

136
00:08:36,375 --> 00:08:37,375
What?

137
00:08:37,709 --> 00:08:39,042
What did you see while passing?

138
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:41,876
You must stay for lunch, okay?

139
00:08:42,542 --> 00:08:44,209
There's nothing wrong with Dad.

140
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,751
Just stop the car
and read that flex board properly.

141
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:49,209
Flex boards aren't
just for funerals, you know!

142
00:08:49,375 --> 00:08:50,375
Okay.

143
00:08:50,918 --> 00:08:51,918
What is it, Thulasi?

144
00:08:52,209 --> 00:08:55,542
Your Dad had asked me to let him know
once the water filter service is done.

145
00:08:55,709 --> 00:08:57,042
Ask them to wait for a bit.

146
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:59,042
I'll tell Dad right after
the Minister leaves.

147
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:04,959
This is my eldest son, Deepankuran.

148
00:09:05,125 --> 00:09:06,500
He was with me at Sabarimala.

149
00:09:06,542 --> 00:09:07,792
Then I must have seen him.

150
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,792
Do you work with your Dad
at the temple here?

151
00:09:09,834 --> 00:09:10,918
Oh no.

152
00:09:10,959 --> 00:09:12,292
He's always abroad.

153
00:09:12,334 --> 00:09:13,959
He handles only VIP pujas.

154
00:09:14,167 --> 00:09:15,417
He's flying to Kenya tonight.

155
00:09:15,459 --> 00:09:16,500
And from there, to Dubai.

156
00:09:16,751 --> 00:09:19,000
He even moved closer
to the airport for convenience.

157
00:09:19,584 --> 00:09:20,834
And this is his wife.

158
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:23,459
Where is your younger son?

159
00:09:24,417 --> 00:09:25,542
He'll be late.

160
00:09:25,584 --> 00:09:27,125
- Let's click the photo.
- Alright.

161
00:09:29,292 --> 00:09:30,292
Sir, over here!

162
00:09:39,959 --> 00:09:41,959
Hey, Pappu!

163
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:45,876
Why are you coming in
from the back, Indu?

164
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:47,876
There were too many people
at the front, Thulasi Chechi.

165
00:09:47,918 --> 00:09:49,042
Dad was there too.

166
00:09:49,417 --> 00:09:50,751
I just wanted to avoid
creating a scene.

167
00:09:51,417 --> 00:09:53,292
And this way,
I could see Pappu too.

168
00:09:53,626 --> 00:09:56,459
Not Pappu.
You have to call him "Uncle Pappu" now.

169
00:09:57,292 --> 00:10:00,167
When your mother brought him here
from behind the temple,

170
00:10:00,209 --> 00:10:02,209
my child
was only four days old then.

171
00:10:02,459 --> 00:10:03,876
She's studying in fifth grade now.

172
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:07,125
He really lost all his cheer
after Mom passed away, didn't he?

173
00:10:07,876 --> 00:10:09,125
Not just him…

174
00:10:09,167 --> 00:10:10,375
You did too.

175
00:10:17,709 --> 00:10:20,626
[Sanskrit news plays on radio]

176
00:10:24,959 --> 00:10:27,375
Sigh! How many times do I have to tell him?

177
00:10:31,751 --> 00:10:32,751
Ugh!

178
00:10:39,542 --> 00:10:40,959
Welcome back, Indu!

179
00:10:42,417 --> 00:10:45,834
You know, if you press that
like this after peeing, it sprays water.

180
00:10:46,209 --> 00:10:47,459
It doesn't even take a second.

181
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:48,959
Why do you have to make
the whole room stink?

182
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:52,125
We're already peeing
into water, aren't we?

183
00:10:52,167 --> 00:10:54,125
So why flush more water in?

184
00:10:55,167 --> 00:10:57,292
Aha! So uncle's favourite is here!

185
00:10:57,751 --> 00:11:00,417
Indu, I need to leave right away
to catch my flight.

186
00:11:00,959 --> 00:11:03,209
Go take a quick shower,
wear a nice mundu,

187
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:04,667
and go take care
of things downstairs.

188
00:11:05,417 --> 00:11:06,918
I have a doubt, Uncle.

189
00:11:06,959 --> 00:11:10,417
For the puja in Kenya, ebony twigs
are required for the sacred fire.

190
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:12,167
That's not easy
to get at the moment.

191
00:11:12,209 --> 00:11:14,042
And we also need
to check in early.

192
00:11:14,167 --> 00:11:15,500
Is there an alternative I can use?

193
00:11:15,542 --> 00:11:17,792
- Isn't it for an auspicious occasion?
- Yes.

194
00:11:17,834 --> 00:11:20,834
Then just use small twigs
from the Bael tree.

195
00:11:21,042 --> 00:11:22,709
That's a relief!
We have Bael in stock.

196
00:11:22,751 --> 00:11:23,959
Okay, so that's sorted.

197
00:11:24,209 --> 00:11:25,918
Want me to bring you anything
from Kenya?

198
00:11:25,959 --> 00:11:28,584
Bring back a Kenyan beauty
for our chronic bachelor here.

199
00:11:28,667 --> 00:11:31,292
Sounds good. Just make sure
she belongs to the Namboothiri clan!

200
00:11:31,334 --> 00:11:33,209
Yeah, right!
High hopes you have!

201
00:11:33,334 --> 00:11:34,792
- Okay. I'll call you, Indu.
- Okay.

202
00:11:35,042 --> 00:11:37,125
- I'll come see you when I'm back.
- Alright, alright.

203
00:11:40,125 --> 00:11:42,667
Deepu Chettan bought
his assistant a car.

204
00:11:43,083 --> 00:11:44,667
I heard he pays him very well, too.

205
00:11:44,876 --> 00:11:47,751
If you still had your sacred thread on,
Deepu would've taken you along.

206
00:11:47,792 --> 00:11:49,417
Had you stayed with Neelakandan,

207
00:11:49,459 --> 00:11:52,334
you would've been the chief priest
of our family temple by now.

208
00:11:52,626 --> 00:11:54,876
Well, it's all because
of the path you chose, isn't it?

209
00:11:56,626 --> 00:11:57,709
At least what I chose...

210
00:11:57,834 --> 00:11:59,626
is something I can feel and hear.

211
00:11:59,959 --> 00:12:01,292
All you have is hype, right?

212
00:12:01,334 --> 00:12:02,542
There's nothing to see or hear.

213
00:12:02,584 --> 00:12:03,584
That's enough.

214
00:12:03,876 --> 00:12:05,417
He's just ignorant!

215
00:12:05,459 --> 00:12:08,500
Forgive this ignorant fool,
O Lord!

216
00:12:09,918 --> 00:12:13,584
And please remind him to flush
after he urinates, O Lord!

217
00:12:15,876 --> 00:12:17,459
Please don't mind!

218
00:12:41,709 --> 00:12:44,042
[Chanting mantras]

219
00:12:56,167 --> 00:12:58,000
Rupesh, the owner of the
shop is this madam here.

220
00:12:58,250 --> 00:12:59,250
Oh!

221
00:13:03,459 --> 00:13:05,792
I'm not saying this just because I did it,
but the puja was a big success.

222
00:13:05,834 --> 00:13:07,042
It's all the Lord's blessing.

223
00:13:07,083 --> 00:13:08,083
Correct.

224
00:13:08,918 --> 00:13:10,209
- Sreekutta...
- Yes.

225
00:13:14,042 --> 00:13:16,584
Hare Krishna, Hare Krishna,
Krishna Krishna Hare Hare.

226
00:13:16,626 --> 00:13:17,626
Hmm!

227
00:13:17,667 --> 00:13:20,125
Hare Rama, Hare Rama,
Rama Rama Hare Hare.

228
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:22,375
Hare Krishna, Hare Krishna,
Krishna Krishna Hare Hare.

229
00:13:22,417 --> 00:13:24,792
Hare Rama, Hare Rama,
Rama Rama Hare Hare.

230
00:13:24,834 --> 00:13:26,042
Hare Krishna, Hare Krishna...

231
00:13:27,626 --> 00:13:28,667
Sreekutta...

232
00:13:28,876 --> 00:13:30,167
You can take it yourself, sir.

233
00:13:32,667 --> 00:13:34,125
I'm not saying this
just because I did it,

234
00:13:34,834 --> 00:13:36,083
but the puja was a big success.

235
00:13:36,167 --> 00:13:37,876
- So?
- So, well...

236
00:13:50,334 --> 00:13:51,792
- Sreekutta...
- Yes.

237
00:13:51,834 --> 00:13:53,375
Just check whether
that broom works.

238
00:13:53,584 --> 00:13:55,250
The broom is in
excellent working condition.

239
00:13:55,292 --> 00:13:56,792
But you'll need to pay me extra
for cleaning.

240
00:13:56,918 --> 00:13:58,709
Don't be so greedy, Sreekutta.

241
00:13:58,751 --> 00:14:00,584
Why shouldn't I be?

242
00:14:00,751 --> 00:14:03,667
Don't I take on
these low-budget pujas for you too?

243
00:14:03,792 --> 00:14:04,626
- Is that so?
- Yes.

244
00:14:04,667 --> 00:14:06,709
Then why were you trying to find
a new assistant instead of me?

245
00:14:06,751 --> 00:14:08,167
No way!
Would I ever do that?

246
00:14:08,209 --> 00:14:09,417
Oh, really?

247
00:14:09,751 --> 00:14:10,751
Just a minute.

248
00:14:13,709 --> 00:14:15,751
Bhasi, that Sreekuttan
is a complete fraud.

249
00:14:15,876 --> 00:14:17,417
Do you know anyone else
who can assist me?

250
00:14:18,125 --> 00:14:20,834
Even if I say all this,
I'm really fond of you.

251
00:14:20,918 --> 00:14:22,876
Of course, I know that,
Rupeshetta!

252
00:14:23,334 --> 00:14:25,292
And that ₹500
the madam gave…

253
00:14:25,334 --> 00:14:26,334
I'm keeping it.

254
00:14:26,375 --> 00:14:27,709
Just consider it
my travel expense.

255
00:14:27,751 --> 00:14:28,918
- Huh?
- Yeah.

256
00:14:30,250 --> 00:14:32,083
- Aren't you happy, Rupeshetta?
- Yes.

257
00:14:32,667 --> 00:14:33,959
I'll get going.
I've got work.

258
00:14:36,292 --> 00:14:37,459
- Pavithran...
- Yes?

259
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:38,751
We need to leave at
4:30 AM tomorrow.

260
00:14:38,792 --> 00:14:39,751
Okay.

261
00:14:39,792 --> 00:14:41,834
Unni, start cutting vegetables
for the Sambar at 3:30 AM.

262
00:14:42,083 --> 00:14:43,083
So where's the feast, Aunty?

263
00:14:43,125 --> 00:14:44,125
In Thrissur.

264
00:14:44,167 --> 00:14:46,417
Oh! You got your bike fixed?

265
00:14:46,459 --> 00:14:47,459
That's great.

266
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:49,209
- I'll be here for a couple of months.
- Okay.

267
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:51,751
The 70th birthday feast
was fantastic, Uncle.

268
00:14:51,792 --> 00:14:53,542
I couldn't eat on a banana leaf
because I arrived late.

269
00:14:53,584 --> 00:14:56,876
Come on! Subramanyan Namboothiri's
feast must be eaten on a banana leaf!

270
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:59,918
It's really embarrassing when you talk
about yourself in the third person, Dad!

271
00:15:01,334 --> 00:15:02,334
Hello!

272
00:15:02,375 --> 00:15:03,709
Give me your phone, Mom.

273
00:15:03,751 --> 00:15:05,292
How's your uncle keeping, Indu?

274
00:15:05,334 --> 00:15:07,500
He's doing well overall.
Only his leg is giving him some trouble.

275
00:15:07,834 --> 00:15:09,083
Hey, do you need a towel?

276
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:10,459
No need. I showered
before I came.

277
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,250
- I'm heading to the temple pond.
- Okay.

278
00:15:12,876 --> 00:15:14,083
Looking handsome!

279
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:16,250
What's on Aunty's mobile phone?

280
00:15:16,626 --> 00:15:18,417
I just checked Anagha's WhatsApp status.

281
00:15:18,959 --> 00:15:20,125
I can't see it.

282
00:15:20,250 --> 00:15:21,667
She blocked me
after we broke up.

283
00:15:21,876 --> 00:15:23,667
- Aren't you ashamed?
- Why should I be?

284
00:15:23,959 --> 00:15:25,709
It's not like I'm bothering her.

285
00:15:26,125 --> 00:15:27,626
Even if we're out
in the semi-finals,

286
00:15:27,667 --> 00:15:29,167
we still need to know
who wins the cup, right?

287
00:15:29,209 --> 00:15:30,334
And don't step on the snake.

288
00:15:31,334 --> 00:15:32,500
- What?
- What?

289
00:15:32,542 --> 00:15:33,792
Ugh! Aren't you ashamed?

290
00:15:40,209 --> 00:15:41,459
- Rupe...
- Yeah?

291
00:15:41,626 --> 00:15:42,876
Do you know of any jobs

292
00:15:42,918 --> 00:15:45,709
that could help me get by
for the next couple of months?

293
00:15:47,709 --> 00:15:49,375
There are many options
in my dad's line of work.

294
00:15:49,918 --> 00:15:51,375
Would you be willing
to serve at feasts?

295
00:15:51,626 --> 00:15:53,918
No, that won't suit me.
Too many people, too much noise…

296
00:15:54,334 --> 00:15:55,751
Do you know
how to grate coconuts?

297
00:15:55,918 --> 00:15:57,209
How about chopping vegetables?

298
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:59,834
No way! If I hurt my hand,
I won't be able to play the guitar.

299
00:16:01,542 --> 00:16:03,209
Why don't you just
work as my assistant?

300
00:16:03,876 --> 00:16:04,876
As a priest's assistant?

301
00:16:04,918 --> 00:16:05,918
That's not happening.

302
00:16:05,959 --> 00:16:09,042
Didn't you and your brother Deepu
study the Vedas properly together?

303
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,918
Even after all this time,
I haven't learned as much as you.

304
00:16:12,209 --> 00:16:13,709
But I'm still able
to keep it going, right?

305
00:16:13,959 --> 00:16:15,250
But that was ages ago.

306
00:16:15,751 --> 00:16:18,500
I'm not really convinced about
this whole "God" concept anymore.

307
00:16:18,876 --> 00:16:21,459
In that case, are you certain
we'll even be alive tomorrow?

308
00:16:21,876 --> 00:16:23,751
That just comes down to luck.

309
00:16:24,167 --> 00:16:25,959
So why not treat
that luck as God?

310
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:29,584
Hey, tell them to buy it
only if they really need it!

311
00:16:29,626 --> 00:16:31,834
[in Hindi] Take it, Bhai.
You'll have fun.

312
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:34,042
[in Hindi]
Bhai, this is quality stuff.

313
00:16:34,792 --> 00:16:35,959
Hey, where are
those guys headed?

314
00:16:36,292 --> 00:16:37,709
This has been going on
for a week.

315
00:16:37,751 --> 00:16:39,459
No fire, no smoke.

316
00:16:39,959 --> 00:16:41,542
Must be hard-core stuff!

317
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:43,334
Here? With me around?

318
00:16:43,375 --> 00:16:44,417
How dare they!

319
00:16:44,459 --> 00:16:47,000
- Rupe...
- I'm not the same Rupa anymore. Move!

320
00:16:47,042 --> 00:16:49,083
Rupe, drop it!
You'll land in trouble!

321
00:16:49,167 --> 00:16:50,334
This is common everywhere!

322
00:16:50,375 --> 00:16:51,417
Just zip it!

323
00:16:51,459 --> 00:16:52,459
Hey! Hey!

324
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:55,042
Who are you guys? Huh?

325
00:16:55,542 --> 00:16:56,667
What's going on here?

326
00:16:56,959 --> 00:16:58,250
Go on! Go home!

327
00:16:58,292 --> 00:16:59,292
Clear out!

328
00:16:59,334 --> 00:17:00,459
Want me to call the cops?

329
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,292
[In Hindi]
Go, go! Go home!

330
00:17:02,667 --> 00:17:03,959
Say something, man.

331
00:17:05,209 --> 00:17:06,334
Who the hell are you guys?

332
00:17:06,584 --> 00:17:09,417
Look at those jeans,
that bag, that chain!

333
00:17:09,584 --> 00:17:11,751
You better cut that hair
and beard tomorrow!

334
00:17:13,709 --> 00:17:15,209
Just chase this pest away.

335
00:17:18,042 --> 00:17:19,042
Scared?

336
00:17:19,834 --> 00:17:21,417
Me? What for?

337
00:17:23,209 --> 00:17:24,209
Oh no!

338
00:17:25,542 --> 00:17:26,584
No, child!
Don't do that!

339
00:17:26,626 --> 00:17:27,876
I said don't!

340
00:17:28,334 --> 00:17:29,334
Oh, Goddess!

341
00:17:29,542 --> 00:17:30,918
Don't! Oh, Goddess!

342
00:17:30,959 --> 00:17:32,500
- Run!
- I am running!

343
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:34,542
That child has such perfect aim!

344
00:17:36,042 --> 00:17:37,876
Indu, I am coming!

345
00:17:37,918 --> 00:17:39,500
Take the soap and towel with you.

346
00:17:42,209 --> 00:17:43,209
Okay.

347
00:17:57,918 --> 00:17:59,876
Chetta, that was awesome!

348
00:17:59,959 --> 00:18:01,751
You elevated the song
to the next level.

349
00:18:01,792 --> 00:18:03,083
It's all because of
the Goddess's grace!

350
00:18:03,125 --> 00:18:04,542
- Right, chetta?
- Yes, yes.

351
00:18:04,792 --> 00:18:06,751
Can I just GPay you?

352
00:18:10,918 --> 00:18:12,209
You don't have cash?

353
00:18:12,792 --> 00:18:14,167
Err... Sanaletta...

354
00:18:14,209 --> 00:18:16,292
We don't have cash.
It'll be credited to your account.

355
00:18:16,334 --> 00:18:17,417
Don't worry.

356
00:18:17,459 --> 00:18:18,459
Nice work.

357
00:18:19,709 --> 00:18:20,792
Psst... Psst!

358
00:18:24,250 --> 00:18:25,709
I've told you so many times

359
00:18:25,751 --> 00:18:27,792
not to call me for these
low-budget music albums.

360
00:18:28,209 --> 00:18:29,209
Oh, I see!

361
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:31,000
You said I should call you
even for a ₹1000 job.

362
00:18:31,042 --> 00:18:32,334
This one pays ₹2500.

363
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,500
- Then where is it?
- It'll come when it comes.

364
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:37,626
I barely have money
to get home, Faizal.

365
00:18:37,959 --> 00:18:39,292
Don't get stressed, Prabha.

366
00:18:39,334 --> 00:18:41,250
Money comes today,
goes tomorrow.

367
00:18:41,876 --> 00:18:43,584
How can it go tomorrow
if it hasn't come today?!

368
00:18:44,459 --> 00:18:45,918
You know the composer
Viraj Trivedi, right?

369
00:18:45,959 --> 00:18:48,584
He's looking for new
electric guitarists from Kerala.

370
00:18:48,876 --> 00:18:50,709
There's a new Malayali girl
in his management team.

371
00:18:50,751 --> 00:18:51,834
That's where this came from.

372
00:18:52,375 --> 00:18:54,667
Remember the session
you did for Justin?

373
00:18:54,959 --> 00:18:56,375
I've already sent it to them!

374
00:18:56,834 --> 00:18:59,292
All his movie and stage-show teams
are from Mumbai.

375
00:18:59,334 --> 00:19:00,334
Photo! Photo!

376
00:19:00,918 --> 00:19:02,584
But it's worth a shot, right?

377
00:19:02,834 --> 00:19:05,167
- What?
- I said, we can try!

378
00:19:05,334 --> 00:19:06,334
Okay.

379
00:19:07,959 --> 00:19:09,792
Is this to check your oxygen level?

380
00:19:09,834 --> 00:19:11,751
It's for credit card verification.

381
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:14,334
- Want one?
- No, no! It's too stressful!

382
00:19:14,375 --> 00:19:16,667
You can withdraw up to
₹60,000 per month, sir.

383
00:19:17,042 --> 00:19:18,083
- Really?
- Yes.

384
00:19:18,167 --> 00:19:19,667
Hell yeah!
Bro, get him one.

385
00:19:20,292 --> 00:19:21,459
What do you do for a living, sir?

386
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:22,500
I'm a musician.

387
00:19:22,542 --> 00:19:24,042
Oh, then you'll definitely be rejected.

388
00:19:24,292 --> 00:19:25,542
- Huh?!
- Sign here.

389
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:27,918
Sir, one photo.

390
00:19:28,918 --> 00:19:29,918
Don't smile so much.

391
00:19:36,042 --> 00:19:37,125
Bro!

392
00:19:37,459 --> 00:19:38,751
You got ₹200?

393
00:19:38,959 --> 00:19:40,751
I went to Ernakulam yesterday
and came back with nothing.

394
00:19:40,792 --> 00:19:41,959
There's zero stock!

395
00:19:42,042 --> 00:19:43,417
How would I have money?!

396
00:19:43,709 --> 00:19:45,375
Why don't you just ask your dad?

397
00:19:45,417 --> 00:19:47,125
Me? Ask him?

398
00:19:47,584 --> 00:19:48,959
Not in this lifetime!

399
00:19:54,918 --> 00:19:55,959
What is it?

400
00:19:57,334 --> 00:19:58,334
Never mind, it's fine.

401
00:19:58,709 --> 00:19:59,709
Who is fine? Me?

402
00:20:00,584 --> 00:20:01,584
Well, not that...

403
00:20:02,667 --> 00:20:04,459
If you have something to say,
just say it.

404
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,000
Do you have change?

405
00:20:06,209 --> 00:20:07,209
How much for?

406
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,751
For... errr... two hundred.

407
00:20:10,792 --> 00:20:12,125
Will two hundreds work?

408
00:20:12,918 --> 00:20:14,500
A single 200 rupee note
is also fine.

409
00:20:14,751 --> 00:20:16,626
Then that isn't really
'change,' is it?

410
00:20:19,834 --> 00:20:20,834
Why do you need it?

411
00:20:21,918 --> 00:20:23,250
Just to step out for a while.

412
00:20:23,417 --> 00:20:25,167
Then why don't you just…
step out?

413
00:20:26,751 --> 00:20:28,209
I was thinking
I'd get a tea as well.

414
00:20:28,250 --> 00:20:29,250
Oh...

415
00:20:29,959 --> 00:20:31,292
- One minute.
- Okay.

416
00:20:36,876 --> 00:20:38,334
You recognise us, don't you?

417
00:20:39,417 --> 00:20:40,417
Of course!

418
00:20:41,292 --> 00:20:42,918
I remember seeing your daughter
when she was very young.

419
00:20:42,959 --> 00:20:43,959
She's grown up so much!

420
00:20:44,417 --> 00:20:46,334
Oh no, she's just my neighbour.

421
00:20:46,375 --> 00:20:47,626
When I told her
we were coming here,

422
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:49,417
she came along
to see your ancestral house.

423
00:20:49,792 --> 00:20:50,959
Yeah, yeah.

424
00:20:52,083 --> 00:20:53,125
Oh, sorry!

425
00:20:53,459 --> 00:20:54,876
You both have a son, right?

426
00:20:55,250 --> 00:20:56,459
This is my brother.

427
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,959
My husband is in Qatar.

428
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:02,626
It's okay.
Don't worry.

429
00:21:05,375 --> 00:21:06,375
Here you go.

430
00:21:06,918 --> 00:21:08,500
There's enough tea
for three cups.

431
00:21:08,751 --> 00:21:10,834
Help yourself
whenever you want.

432
00:21:11,417 --> 00:21:12,459
Okay?

433
00:21:14,334 --> 00:21:17,042
Back in our day, if Father knew
I drank tea from outside,

434
00:21:17,083 --> 00:21:18,500
I'd get beaten instantly.

435
00:21:18,751 --> 00:21:21,083
Kids these days...

436
00:21:21,334 --> 00:21:22,459
they are just different.

437
00:21:24,417 --> 00:21:25,584
That was funny!

438
00:21:25,792 --> 00:21:28,334
Weren't you the first one
to gain fame here, Prahladan Namboothiri?

439
00:21:28,375 --> 00:21:30,500
Even my father
started off as your assistant, right?

440
00:21:30,584 --> 00:21:31,584
So what?

441
00:21:31,918 --> 00:21:34,209
How do you put up with Dad's
attitude and still stay here?

442
00:21:34,292 --> 00:21:36,500
Because I'm very fond of myself.

443
00:21:37,083 --> 00:21:38,083
Huh?!

444
00:21:38,209 --> 00:21:39,667
What do we really want in life?

445
00:21:39,959 --> 00:21:43,959
Someone who loves us dearly,
and takes good care of us.

446
00:21:44,250 --> 00:21:45,250
Right?

447
00:21:45,918 --> 00:21:46,918
Yes.

448
00:21:46,959 --> 00:21:48,584
Why can't I be that person?

449
00:21:48,918 --> 00:21:50,834
I love myself dearly.

450
00:21:50,959 --> 00:21:52,626
And I take very good care of myself.

451
00:21:52,834 --> 00:21:54,334
You don't care about anyone but yourself!

452
00:21:54,417 --> 00:21:55,918
You have no idea what
I'm going through!

453
00:21:58,584 --> 00:22:01,584
[quotes a sloka from the Mahabharata]

454
00:22:04,250 --> 00:22:05,250
What comes next?

455
00:22:05,751 --> 00:22:07,751
Say it out loud.
Don't you know this sloka?

456
00:22:09,167 --> 00:22:12,334
[completes the sloka]

457
00:22:13,959 --> 00:22:15,209
What does it mean?

458
00:22:18,167 --> 00:22:20,000
No crisis can take away
your ability to think.

459
00:22:20,876 --> 00:22:23,167
If you apply that ability,
wealth can be earned again.

460
00:22:23,250 --> 00:22:24,250
Simple.

461
00:22:24,542 --> 00:22:25,792
That's it.

462
00:22:25,918 --> 00:22:27,459
Now go on, earn.

463
00:22:37,834 --> 00:22:38,834
Aunty, where's Rupesh?

464
00:22:38,876 --> 00:22:40,209
He's bathing in our pond.

465
00:22:40,375 --> 00:22:42,709
I don't know why...
He's stopped going to the temple pond.

466
00:22:46,709 --> 00:22:47,751
Rupe...

467
00:22:48,167 --> 00:22:49,167
Yeah?

468
00:22:50,334 --> 00:22:51,375
I'm ready.

469
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:52,500
Ready for what?

470
00:22:52,834 --> 00:22:55,250
I'm ready to put on
the sacred thread

471
00:22:56,083 --> 00:22:57,209
and perform pujas.

472
