"We must loosen the tangles,
undo all the knots…"

502
00:25:18,209 --> 00:25:20,500
"We must chant the mantra fearlessly,
and must rise to our victory"

503
00:25:20,918 --> 00:25:25,375
"Let us move forward,
ahead of the rest"

504
00:25:25,626 --> 00:25:30,209
"By your own true being,
Blaze forth as lightning at its best"

505
00:25:30,751 --> 00:25:35,459
"As time's own phases onward glide,
as your rituals flow in a faithful tide"

506
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:40,209
"As your deeds take form on life's broad shelf,
discover yourself within your self"

507
00:25:49,959 --> 00:25:52,042
"The crystal-clear star
in the heavens so bright"

508
00:25:52,083 --> 00:25:54,584
"It's holding its solemn vigil
in worshipful light"

509
00:25:54,751 --> 00:25:56,792
"To the tune of the soft chant
in gentle sway"

510
00:25:56,834 --> 00:25:59,250
"That blooms on the tongue's tip
in a blossoming way"

511
00:25:59,334 --> 00:26:01,334
Run! Run! Catch him!

512
00:26:03,209 --> 00:26:04,500
- Indu...
- Yeah?

513
00:26:04,542 --> 00:26:05,834
I just noticed something.

514
00:26:05,876 --> 00:26:07,500
Has your accent changed slightly?

515
00:26:07,751 --> 00:26:09,083
- Is that what has come to pass?
- Yes!

516
00:26:09,125 --> 00:26:10,584
Exactly!
That's our traditional accent.

517
00:26:10,626 --> 00:26:12,083
Does that really matter?

518
00:26:13,083 --> 00:26:14,959
Priest, breakfast is ready.

519
00:26:15,083 --> 00:26:16,876
- Please have it before you leave.
- Is that so?

520
00:26:17,334 --> 00:26:19,459
- Can't we just eat at home later?
- There's only Upma at home.

521
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:21,876
It's masala dosa here.
I'll be right back.

522
00:26:22,042 --> 00:26:23,042
Oh dear...

523
00:26:23,834 --> 00:26:24,834
Five, six...

524
00:26:24,918 --> 00:26:26,584
6 x 5 = 36...
It's okay.

525
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:27,876
Move.

526
00:26:27,918 --> 00:26:29,083
This looks good!

527
00:26:29,125 --> 00:26:30,709
- Did you make this, Paulose?
- Yes.

528
00:26:30,918 --> 00:26:31,918
- Is it made of teak?
- Yes.

529
00:26:31,959 --> 00:26:33,626
Paulose insists it's teak.

530
00:26:33,709 --> 00:26:35,083
Then it must've cost a lot.

531
00:26:35,125 --> 00:26:37,292
Anything Paulose builds
never comes cheap, right?

532
00:26:37,459 --> 00:26:38,709
I just hope it's sturdy enough.

533
00:26:38,751 --> 00:26:40,751
It's sturdier than
the wig on your head.

534
00:26:40,834 --> 00:26:42,918
Better hold on to it.
Don't let it fly away.

535
00:26:43,292 --> 00:26:45,542
How many people can
sit on this, Paulose?

536
00:26:45,584 --> 00:26:48,667
It won't move an inch
even if the whole village sits on it.

537
00:26:48,709 --> 00:26:50,459
Stop exaggerating, Paulose!

538
00:26:50,584 --> 00:26:51,959
Me? Exaggerating?

539
00:26:52,209 --> 00:26:53,209
Please step aside, sir.

540
00:26:53,375 --> 00:26:54,584
I'll prove it now!

541
00:26:54,626 --> 00:26:55,626
All of you, move aside.

542
00:26:55,959 --> 00:26:56,959
Come here, son.

543
00:26:57,167 --> 00:26:58,167
You sit there.

544
00:26:58,375 --> 00:26:59,709
All you kids,
go and sit.

545
00:26:59,751 --> 00:27:01,167
Go sit, Chechi.
Go on.

546
00:27:01,542 --> 00:27:02,959
Come on, everyone.
Come and sit.

547
00:27:03,626 --> 00:27:05,334
- What? You want to sit, Priest?
- No, no.

548
00:27:05,459 --> 00:27:06,876
Please sit.
It'll be an honour.

549
00:27:06,918 --> 00:27:08,167
Move aside.
Let the priest sit.

550
00:27:08,209 --> 00:27:09,542
- No, really...
- Go on, sit.

551
00:27:10,042 --> 00:27:10,959
How about now?

552
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,125
Call your dad or mom,
whoever's around.

553
00:27:13,209 --> 00:27:14,417
Let them try swinging on it.

554
00:27:16,542 --> 00:27:17,542
Psst...

555
00:27:17,667 --> 00:27:18,667
Coming?

556
00:27:22,834 --> 00:27:24,542
Come here, big shot!

557
00:27:25,709 --> 00:27:26,667
Give it a good push!

558
00:27:26,709 --> 00:27:27,500
Oh my!

559
00:27:27,542 --> 00:27:28,459
Oh no!

560
00:27:31,709 --> 00:27:33,292
Nothing to worry!

561
00:27:33,334 --> 00:27:34,500
The swing is perfectly fine.

562
00:27:37,125 --> 00:27:38,167
Go on, cry again.

563
00:27:39,626 --> 00:27:40,626
Shush!

564
00:27:44,375 --> 00:27:45,500
Move, move!

565
00:27:51,709 --> 00:27:52,709
Rupe!

566
00:27:56,709 --> 00:27:57,834
Does it hurt, son?

567
00:27:58,000 --> 00:27:59,000
Not at all.

568
00:27:59,334 --> 00:28:02,250
The doctor said the MRI scan showed
nothing wrong with his head.

569
00:28:02,500 --> 00:28:04,250
Such a waste of money!

570
00:28:04,667 --> 00:28:05,751
At least the X-ray
was worth it.

571
00:28:05,792 --> 00:28:07,500
It shows swelling at two spots
on his spine.

572
00:28:08,292 --> 00:28:11,209
Luckily, with Indu around, all the
pujas you agreed to won't be cancelled.

573
00:28:11,292 --> 00:28:12,292
- Yes.
- Hmm.

574
00:28:13,250 --> 00:28:14,918
Now, if you both could step outside.

575
00:28:15,417 --> 00:28:17,417
I need to talk to Indu in private.

576
00:28:17,667 --> 00:28:18,667
Go on.

577
00:28:19,959 --> 00:28:21,000
Go on, Mom!

578
00:28:21,584 --> 00:28:22,584
Let's go.

579
00:28:24,542 --> 00:28:25,584
Indu

580
00:28:28,500 --> 00:28:29,542
- Indu...
- Yeah?

581
00:28:29,834 --> 00:28:31,626
Yes, I'm your cousin.

582
00:28:32,209 --> 00:28:33,209
But now...

583
00:28:33,834 --> 00:28:34,876
Now what?

584
00:28:34,918 --> 00:28:37,125
Now I'm your employer too.

585
00:28:37,417 --> 00:28:38,417
So what?

586
00:28:39,292 --> 00:28:42,125
You're fully capable
of doing pujas on your own now,

587
00:28:42,667 --> 00:28:44,083
and making your own money.

588
00:28:44,584 --> 00:28:45,959
That makes me proud.

589
00:28:46,417 --> 00:28:48,542
Look, I'm not planning
to do this forever.

590
00:28:48,792 --> 00:28:50,667
I'll leave once
I'm financially stable.

591
00:28:50,751 --> 00:28:51,876
Sure, you can leave.

592
00:28:51,918 --> 00:28:53,542
That's not my point.

593
00:28:53,918 --> 00:28:56,417
From tomorrow, we split
whatever you earn from the pujas,

594
00:28:56,459 --> 00:28:57,834
fifty-fifty.

595
00:28:58,125 --> 00:28:58,959
Huh?!

596
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:00,042
But I'm the one
doing the puja!

597
00:29:00,083 --> 00:29:01,876
And I'm the one
bringing in the clients, right?

598
00:29:01,918 --> 00:29:03,209
- Rupe!
- Listen, Indu...

599
00:29:03,417 --> 00:29:06,626
When family and friends
turn into business partners,

600
00:29:06,667 --> 00:29:09,292
having clarity about financial matters

601
00:29:09,417 --> 00:29:10,959
can help prevent future conflicts.

602
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:13,292
There's no point
spoiling our relationship over it.

603
00:29:13,334 --> 00:29:14,334
That's all I wanted to say.

604
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:18,459
- 60-40.
- Yeah, that's fine. Fine.

605
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:19,500
40 is fine, 40 is fine.

606
00:29:20,709 --> 00:29:21,792
You are happy, right?

607
00:29:45,918 --> 00:29:50,209
"It clears up like the sky
in its vast renew"

608
00:29:50,667 --> 00:29:54,959
"It fills like the ocean of milk
breaking through"

609
00:29:55,459 --> 00:29:59,751
"Ascend the chariot of that wisdom
alive within you"

610
00:30:00,334 --> 00:30:04,459
"And continue your journey,
steady and true"

611
00:30:04,500 --> 00:30:09,042
"Every single battle
that comes our way"

612
00:30:09,334 --> 00:30:13,417
"Let us face it with
blazing determination each day"

613
00:30:14,459 --> 00:30:19,042
"On the stylus tip where thought arises,
what counts as truth, what slips as lies"

614
00:30:19,292 --> 00:30:23,959
"Don't worry about any of that today,
Just turn to yourself, be yourself your way"

615
00:30:33,667 --> 00:30:35,751
"The crystal-clear star
in the heavens so bright"

616
00:30:35,792 --> 00:30:38,167
"It's holding its solemn vigil
in worshipful light"

617
00:30:38,417 --> 00:30:40,500
"To the tune of the soft chant
in gentle sway"

618
00:30:40,542 --> 00:30:42,959
"That blooms on the tongue's tip
in a blossoming way"

619
00:30:43,292 --> 00:30:45,334
"Within the realm of fading memories
that drift like shade"

620
00:30:45,375 --> 00:30:47,459
"The Vedas endure,
refusing to fade"

621
00:30:48,083 --> 00:30:50,125
"Counting them one by one
as patterns shift"

622
00:30:50,167 --> 00:30:52,792
"Habits change,
letting the unwanted drift"

623
00:31:01,334 --> 00:31:02,334
Prabha...
Just a minute.

624
00:31:02,375 --> 00:31:03,542
- Almost done.
- Okay.

625
00:31:03,876 --> 00:31:04,876
Hey, Prabha...

626
00:31:05,042 --> 00:31:06,000
Faizal told me.

627
00:31:06,042 --> 00:31:07,042
Congrats!

628
00:31:07,083 --> 00:31:08,834
Don't forget us
when you make it big in Bombay!

629
00:31:08,876 --> 00:31:10,334
Oh, come on!

630
00:31:13,792 --> 00:31:14,834
Hey...

631
00:31:14,876 --> 00:31:17,500
I've sent you a
request on Instagram.

632
00:31:18,584 --> 00:31:19,959
I'm not very active on it.

633
00:31:20,042 --> 00:31:21,500
Well, you can just accept it
right now.

634
00:31:24,250 --> 00:31:25,584
Oh... just a minute.

635
00:31:28,626 --> 00:31:29,626
Hey, Rupe...

636
00:31:29,667 --> 00:31:31,167
Indu, where are you?

637
00:31:31,417 --> 00:31:34,500
Remember I told you about
Viraj Trivedi, the Hindi music director?

638
00:31:34,751 --> 00:31:36,751
He loved the track
I sent him.

639
00:31:37,125 --> 00:31:39,250
He has called me to the studio
for a video call session.

640
00:31:39,542 --> 00:31:41,334
Wow, congrats!
That's amazing!

641
00:31:41,626 --> 00:31:43,417
What are you doing
tomorrow evening?

642
00:31:43,500 --> 00:31:45,792
I've got a Ganesha Puja
at Kadampuzha at dawn.

643
00:31:46,125 --> 00:31:47,751
I thought I'd watch a movie
later in the evening.

644
00:31:47,792 --> 00:31:49,626
Ugh! That's a horrible movie!

645
00:31:49,834 --> 00:31:51,459
But I never told you
which movie it was!

646
00:31:51,626 --> 00:31:52,626
Oh, you didn't?

647
00:31:52,959 --> 00:31:54,959
- He didn't!
- Yeah, you didn't.

648
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:56,042
Anyway, listen...

649
00:31:56,083 --> 00:31:58,083
Can you handle
one more puja tomorrow?

650
00:31:58,459 --> 00:31:59,709
You can go after 6:00 PM.

651
00:32:00,459 --> 00:32:01,500
The pay is huge!

652
00:32:01,542 --> 00:32:04,459
The biggest one our astrologer
Krishnanunni has ever given us!

653
00:32:04,626 --> 00:32:05,667
What kind of puja?

654
00:32:06,167 --> 00:32:08,042
A lawyer from Palakkad...

655
00:32:08,334 --> 00:32:10,876
His son who's a 12th grade student,
is said to be possessed.

656
00:32:11,125 --> 00:32:13,083
He's been seeing and hearing things.

657
00:32:13,375 --> 00:32:15,500
Rupe, I honestly don't know
anything about exorcisms.

658
00:32:15,542 --> 00:32:17,083
Hey, I'll walk you through it.

659
00:32:17,125 --> 00:32:21,417
I'll send you a PDF on WhatsApp
with updated chants and procedures.

660
00:32:21,500 --> 00:32:23,834
Otherwise, it's the same
Sudarshana Homam setup.

661
00:32:23,876 --> 00:32:26,292
Just add more fire and flowers
for extra punch.

662
00:32:28,292 --> 00:32:30,751
Sometimes I wonder why we named
you 'Rupe'. You're obsessed with money.

663
00:32:30,792 --> 00:32:32,167
How is that my fault?

664
00:32:32,500 --> 00:32:33,500
Hey... please!

665
00:32:34,083 --> 00:32:35,042
Alright.

666
00:32:35,083 --> 00:32:36,500
- And hey, don't forget... 60-40.

667
00:32:36,709 --> 00:32:37,709
Yeah, okay.

668
00:32:38,626 --> 00:32:39,667
Hey Prabha...

669
00:32:39,959 --> 00:32:41,334
Sorry, man. Not today.

670
00:32:41,626 --> 00:32:43,042
Viraj sir's manager just called.

671
00:32:43,083 --> 00:32:45,334
He worked through the night
and is sleeping during the day.

672
00:32:46,542 --> 00:32:47,542
Okay.

673
00:32:48,125 --> 00:32:50,042
That's fine.
Just keep me posted next time.

674
00:32:50,209 --> 00:32:51,209
Okay?

675
00:32:51,584 --> 00:32:52,584
Okay.

676
00:32:54,250 --> 00:32:55,250
So...

677
00:32:55,292 --> 00:32:57,375
Can you add my Insta ID now?

678
00:32:57,417 --> 00:32:58,417
Chokichosky.

679
00:32:58,459 --> 00:32:59,876
Chokay... I mean, okay.

680
00:33:01,417 --> 00:33:02,959
[Straight from the heart]

681
00:33:03,250 --> 00:33:05,417
If you're going for physiotherapy,
use the car.

682
00:33:05,459 --> 00:33:08,334
Ha! It's such a struggle for me
to climb down into that low car

683
00:33:08,375 --> 00:33:09,584
and then haul myself back up.

684
00:33:10,042 --> 00:33:12,042
An auto rickshaw is far
more comfortable.

685
00:33:12,792 --> 00:33:14,500
Don't you have a puja today?

686
00:33:14,542 --> 00:33:15,584
Yes.

687
00:33:15,626 --> 00:33:16,876
- Be careful.
- Okay.

688
00:33:17,834 --> 00:33:20,709
What, am I supposed
to drive it myself now?

689
00:33:24,459 --> 00:33:26,542
Hey, what's all this
you've been chopping off?

690
00:33:26,584 --> 00:33:27,792
Will you destroy all the plants?

691
00:33:27,834 --> 00:33:29,500
For the plants,
this is just like a haircut.

692
00:33:29,542 --> 00:33:30,709
They might even
be enjoying it.

693
00:33:30,918 --> 00:33:32,334
I'm crazy about plants, you know.

694
00:33:32,375 --> 00:33:33,375
Shall we go?

695
00:33:35,042 --> 00:33:36,042
Name?

696
00:33:37,250 --> 00:33:38,876
Hibiscus rosa-sinensis.

697
00:33:38,918 --> 00:33:39,959
It's also called "China Rose".

698
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:41,959
Not that!
What's your name?

699
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,042
Oh!

700
00:33:43,209 --> 00:33:44,209
I'm Animon.

701
00:33:44,751 --> 00:33:46,626
- Ready to go?
- Yeah, let's go.

702
00:33:50,542 --> 00:33:52,709
Feel free to take the car
when you go for your pujas.

703
00:33:54,209 --> 00:33:56,250
It's okay.
I'll just go in this auto.

704
00:34:06,042 --> 00:34:07,709
What puja is happening
so late, sir?

705
00:34:07,751 --> 00:34:08,751
Is it for the Goddess?

706
00:34:08,918 --> 00:34:10,500
No! It's an exorcism.

707
00:34:17,042 --> 00:34:18,667
- Advocate Dileep?
- Yes.

708
00:34:18,709 --> 00:34:19,918
Rupesh had called.

709
00:34:20,876 --> 00:34:22,500
Need a hand with your supplies?

710
00:34:22,542 --> 00:34:23,876
No, it's fine.
I have someone with--

711
00:34:28,167 --> 00:34:29,417
I'll call the driver.

712
00:34:42,959 --> 00:34:43,959
Can I keep this here?

713
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:45,083
Yes, please.

714
00:34:46,542 --> 00:34:47,959
Just the grass mat is left, right?

715
00:34:48,042 --> 00:34:49,042
Yes, that's it.

716
00:34:49,918 --> 00:34:51,667
- You can bring the boy in 10 minutes.
- Okay.

717
00:34:55,250 --> 00:34:56,250
Deepthi Chechi!

718
00:34:59,042 --> 00:35:00,042
Here you go.

719
00:35:00,709 --> 00:35:02,083
It'll be ready in 10 minutes.

720
00:35:05,167 --> 00:35:06,167
Alright.

721
00:35:12,959 --> 00:35:14,459
Do you practice
at the District Court here?

722
00:35:14,500 --> 00:35:15,876
Yes, for the past two months.

723
00:35:16,334 --> 00:35:18,125
- I'm from Kuttikkanam.
- I see.

724
00:35:21,417 --> 00:35:22,542
Whose guitar is that?

725
00:35:22,709 --> 00:35:23,834
That's Kuttu's.

726
00:35:24,167 --> 00:35:25,500
Ah... I mean, Avinash.

727
00:35:26,042 --> 00:35:27,292
He plays really well.

728
00:35:27,417 --> 00:35:30,417
He always says,
"I'm hungry, Latha Chechi."

729
00:35:30,459 --> 00:35:31,709
Now, he has zero appetite.

730
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:34,042
Oh.

731
00:35:34,083 --> 00:35:35,459
Didn't you take him
to a doctor?

732
00:35:35,500 --> 00:35:37,626
We did. There's a doctor
at NIMHANS.

733
00:35:37,667 --> 00:35:39,167
Dr. Raphael.
He's brilliant.

734
00:35:39,709 --> 00:35:40,834
We consulted him.

735
00:35:40,876 --> 00:35:42,125
Kuttu is on medication too.

736
00:35:42,459 --> 00:35:45,709
But my wife insisted
on having this puja done.

737
00:35:45,918 --> 00:35:47,626
I don't really believe in any of this.

738
00:35:59,876 --> 00:36:00,876
You can sit.

739
00:36:01,834 --> 00:36:03,459
Kutta... Sit down, son.

740
00:36:07,209 --> 00:36:08,209
Sit down.

741
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:10,083
You can sit with him, Ma'am.

742
00:36:10,125 --> 00:36:11,417
That will make him
more comfortable.

743
00:36:12,459 --> 00:36:13,459
Sit down, son.

744
00:36:19,792 --> 00:36:21,000
When did all this begin?

745
00:36:21,125 --> 00:36:22,375
It's been about a week now.

746
00:36:22,792 --> 00:36:25,626
One night, he walked into our room crying
and lay down beside us.

747
00:36:27,167 --> 00:36:30,167
He says someone keeps approaching him,
trying to say something.

748
00:36:32,125 --> 00:36:33,292
A man or a woman?

749
00:36:33,626 --> 00:36:34,751
It's a young girl.

750
00:36:35,500 --> 00:36:38,209
Now he needs me with him 24/7.

751
00:36:39,209 --> 00:36:40,584
Even when he goes
to the bathroom!

752
00:36:44,459 --> 00:36:45,500
Hello!

753
00:36:48,042 --> 00:36:49,834
He makes no eye contact at all now.

754
00:36:51,626 --> 00:36:52,626
I see.

755
00:36:56,375 --> 00:36:57,709
We're about to begin the puja.

756
00:36:58,292 --> 00:37:00,459
The spiritual reading suggests
this is a case of possession.

757
00:37:01,500 --> 00:37:02,876
Once this puja is complete,

758
00:37:02,918 --> 00:37:05,709
the spirit will leave his body
and merge with the supreme.

759
00:38:24,334 --> 00:38:25,334
Hi Latha Chechi...

760
00:38:26,125 --> 00:38:27,125
Huh?

761
00:38:39,125 --> 00:38:41,375
Kuttu! Oh, my son!

762
00:38:42,459 --> 00:38:43,918
Latha, are you seeing this?

763
00:38:44,417 --> 00:38:45,459
It worked?

764
00:38:45,500 --> 00:38:46,542
Dileepetta!

765
00:38:46,584 --> 00:38:48,042
That's not possible!

766
00:38:48,918 --> 00:38:51,626
- Look, our son!
- Hey, Kuttu! Are you okay?

767
00:38:51,667 --> 00:38:52,709
Yeah, I am okay.

768
00:38:53,626 --> 00:38:54,626
Deepthi!

769
00:38:55,083 --> 00:38:56,417
See? Didn't I tell you?

770
00:39:06,500 --> 00:39:10,918
[internalized sacred echoes]

771
00:39:15,167 --> 00:39:16,209
- Gho...
- Gho...

772
00:39:16,918 --> 00:39:17,918
Go on, say it.

773
00:39:18,792 --> 00:39:19,834
You go ahead.

774
00:39:20,250 --> 00:39:21,626
The ghost is definitely gone.

775
00:39:22,334 --> 00:39:24,709
All the chants I sent you
worked like a charm.

776
00:39:24,876 --> 00:39:27,209
Oh, come on! They had already
consulted a doctor.

777
00:39:27,667 --> 00:39:30,125
I think the medicine
finally kicked in.

778
00:39:30,959 --> 00:39:31,959
Oh...

779
00:39:32,375 --> 00:39:37,626
Still, if that lawyer paid ₹1 lakh
instead of the ₹60,000 we asked…

780
00:39:37,959 --> 00:39:39,459
- Indu...
- What?

781
00:39:40,167 --> 00:39:42,375
Ever since you started wearing
the sacred thread and doing pujas,

782
00:39:42,417 --> 00:39:44,792
don't you feel some
kind of divine presence?

783
00:39:45,918 --> 00:39:47,959
I see this as
a job I'm paid for.

784
00:39:48,250 --> 00:39:50,375
So shouldn't I just be sincere,
stay disciplined,

785
00:39:50,417 --> 00:39:53,125
and do the job I was hired for
as honestly as I can?

786
00:39:53,167 --> 00:39:55,542
- You should.
- That's what this 'presence' means to me.

787
00:39:55,667 --> 00:39:56,667
Oh.

788
00:39:56,918 --> 00:39:57,918
I'm leaving.

789
00:39:57,959 --> 00:39:59,792
And I need a three-day break,
starting day after tomorrow.

790
00:39:59,834 --> 00:40:00,834
Oh no, no, no!

791
00:40:00,918 --> 00:40:02,417
I've already scheduled
three pujas for you!

792
00:40:02,459 --> 00:40:04,292
- Take your break after that.
- No! No way!

793
00:40:04,500 --> 00:40:05,751
How about 60-40?

794
00:40:06,417 --> 00:40:08,000
- 70-30.
- Okay.

795
00:40:12,709 --> 00:40:13,876
Mom, give me your phone.

796
00:40:13,918 --> 00:40:15,459
She hasn't posted
any status update today!

797
00:40:15,500 --> 00:40:16,500
Oh.

798
00:40:29,918 --> 00:40:30,959
Hello?

799
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:33,751
There are several types of
silver idols here for today's ritual.

800
00:40:34,292 --> 00:40:35,417
I've sent you the photos.

801
00:40:35,459 --> 00:40:36,459
Which one should I get?

802
00:40:36,709 --> 00:40:37,751
Oh, just a second.

803
00:40:44,459 --> 00:40:45,459
Get the smallest one.

804
00:40:45,542 --> 00:40:47,083
Okay, okay.
I'll take this one.

805
00:40:47,459 --> 00:40:50,876
By the way, who's that Chinese fellow
in your WhatsApp DP?

806
00:40:51,751 --> 00:40:52,751
Chinese fellow?

807
00:41:02,959 --> 00:41:04,292
He's a Korean singer.

808
00:41:04,709 --> 00:41:06,000
Oh, I see.

809
00:41:06,292 --> 00:41:08,250
For a moment, I thought
I'd called the wrong person.

810
00:41:08,542 --> 00:41:09,876
- Alright then.
- Okay.

811
00:41:14,709 --> 00:41:15,751
Thank you.

812
00:41:16,083 --> 00:41:17,083
Okay.

813
00:41:32,626 --> 00:41:33,626
Hello.

814
00:41:33,876 --> 00:41:35,083
You're Prabhendu, aren't you?

815
00:41:35,500 --> 00:41:36,500
I'm Sreekuttan.

816
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:38,292
I used to be
Rupeshettan's assistant.

817
00:41:38,792 --> 00:41:39,792
Oh!

818
00:41:39,834 --> 00:41:41,459
Rupeshettan used
to talk about a cousin

819
00:41:41,500 --> 00:41:42,834
who left home twelve years ago,

820
00:41:43,125 --> 00:41:46,334
threw away his sacred thread, and has
been wandering around playing the guitar.

821
00:41:47,792 --> 00:41:48,792
So that's you, huh?

822
00:41:49,709 --> 00:41:51,417
And on top of that, you're an atheist!

823
00:41:52,334 --> 00:41:53,500
Good heavens!

824
00:41:54,042 --> 00:41:55,375
Let's keep this between us.

825
00:41:57,292 --> 00:41:59,959
So what if I charge a little extra?

826
00:42:00,125 --> 00:42:01,834
You're better off with me by your side.

827
00:42:02,500 --> 00:42:03,542
Okay, right?

828
00:42:05,125 --> 00:42:06,375
Yes, we're okay!

829
00:42:32,125 --> 00:42:35,250
[indistinct chatter]

830
00:42:35,292 --> 00:42:36,626
Oh dear...
Come on

831
00:42:37,042 --> 00:42:38,417
What just happened?

832
00:42:38,834 --> 00:42:40,334
He must be hurt.
Move, move.

833
00:42:40,375 --> 00:42:41,918
[indistinct chatter]

834
00:42:42,500 --> 00:42:44,167
- Are you hurt?
- You're okay, right?

835
00:42:44,375 --> 00:42:46,459
- Hello!
- Is he okay?

836
00:42:49,959 --> 00:42:51,167
Oh Goddess!

837
00:42:52,667 --> 00:42:54,834
If I've done anything wrong
without meaning to,

838
00:42:55,459 --> 00:42:56,959
please forgive me, Priest.

839
00:42:58,751 --> 00:42:59,751
Let's go.

840
00:43:07,292 --> 00:43:08,584
Chechi, are you Prabhendu?

841
00:43:08,792 --> 00:43:11,167
- Huh?
- I asked if you're Prabhendu.

842
00:43:11,250 --> 00:43:13,083
- No. Why?
- I have a parcel for Prabhendu.

843
00:43:13,584 --> 00:43:15,083
- Give it to me.
- To you?

844
00:43:15,167 --> 00:43:17,125
- What's the problem?
- Go call Prabhendu Chechi.

845
00:43:17,167 --> 00:43:18,417
I'll hand it over to her myself.

846
00:43:18,500 --> 00:43:19,834
Not Chechi.
He's a Chettan.

847
00:43:20,334 --> 00:43:21,751
- Chettan?
- Yes.

848
00:43:22,459 --> 00:43:23,918
Alright. Go call him then.

849
00:43:24,167 --> 00:43:25,834
I'll make sure
the crows don't peck it.

850
00:43:26,667 --> 00:43:27,792
Wait here.

851
00:43:29,751 --> 00:43:31,292
There's a parcel for you, Indutty.

852
00:43:33,125 --> 00:43:34,375
For me?
What could it be?

853
00:43:36,792 --> 00:43:37,918
I haven't ordered anything!

854
00:43:37,959 --> 00:43:39,125
Maybe you've got the wrong address.

855
00:43:39,167 --> 00:43:41,626
Prabhendu N. Namboothiri,
Mullasseri House.

856
00:43:41,667 --> 00:43:42,709
That's you, right?

857
00:43:42,876 --> 00:43:44,083
- Yeah.
- Here you go.

858
00:43:47,209 --> 00:43:49,125
But I don't even have your app
on my phone...

859
00:43:50,250 --> 00:43:51,083
It's there, right?

860
00:43:51,125 --> 00:43:52,626
You'll get an OTP.
Can you read it out?

861
00:43:54,125 --> 00:43:56,209
- 6, 2, 0...
- 6, 2, 0...

862
00:43:56,250 --> 00:43:58,250
- 4, 0, 9.
- 4, 0, 9.

863
00:43:58,417 --> 00:44:00,209
- Okay.
- Wait, what about the payment?

864
00:44:00,375 --> 00:44:01,459
That's already done.

865
00:44:01,959 --> 00:44:03,667
Payment was through credit card.

866
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:06,500
Credit card?
But I never added my credit card to--

867
00:44:07,250 --> 00:44:08,751
So that's saved too?

868
00:44:09,417 --> 00:44:10,667
This is clearly a mistake.

869
00:44:11,042 --> 00:44:11,959
Please return this.

870
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:13,334
I can't just take it back.

871
00:44:13,375 --> 00:44:15,167
I need a return token
from the company.

872
00:44:15,292 --> 00:44:16,542
That'll take a couple of days.

873
00:44:17,042 --> 00:44:18,626
I swear, I didn't order this.

874
00:44:18,667 --> 00:44:20,167
Sir, if you have a complaint,

875
00:44:20,209 --> 00:44:22,834
take your time
and call customer care.

876
00:44:22,876 --> 00:44:24,292
That's what they're there for, right?

877
00:44:32,959 --> 00:44:35,292
What's going on with your phone?
You've been glued to it for a while.

878
00:44:36,500 --> 00:44:40,584
I'm just deleting some unnecessary apps
from my phone, Uncle.

879
00:44:41,375 --> 00:44:43,042
The WhatsApp photo keeps
changing on its own!

880
00:44:43,375 --> 00:44:46,667
It's downloading apps on its own
and ordering clothes with my credit card!

881
00:44:47,292 --> 00:44:49,042
Must be some Chinese app.

882
00:44:50,959 --> 00:44:51,959
Did you lose any money?

883
00:44:52,417 --> 00:44:53,417
Yup.

884
00:44:53,959 --> 00:44:55,375
I've requested a refund.

885
00:44:55,834 --> 00:44:56,834
Hopefully it comes through.

886
00:45:41,167 --> 00:45:42,167
Hi!

887
00:45:46,375 --> 00:45:47,959
Hey, don't panic.

888
00:45:50,209 --> 00:45:51,459
I'll go and come back later.

889
00:45:55,334 --> 00:45:56,417
Bye!

890
00:46:47,667 --> 00:46:49,584
Why did you sleep here last night?

891
00:46:49,626 --> 00:46:51,083
What's with this sudden affection?

892
00:46:52,959 --> 00:46:54,709
I had a dream last night.

893
00:46:55,751 --> 00:46:56,751
It really shook me.

894
00:46:56,792 --> 00:46:57,918
Oh!

895
00:46:58,250 --> 00:46:59,292
There was a girl...

896
00:47:01,042 --> 00:47:02,542
She was just sitting there, staring at me.

897
00:47:03,584 --> 00:47:04,876
A very beautiful girl.

898
00:47:05,083 --> 00:47:08,250
That's a standard dream for bachelors
well past their marriage age.

899
00:47:08,500 --> 00:47:10,500
Even at my age,
I get such dreams.

900
00:47:10,542 --> 00:47:11,542
So naturally, you would too!

901
00:47:12,334 --> 00:47:13,459
This wasn't like that.

902
00:47:13,959 --> 00:47:16,459
I even heard her voice clearly.

903
00:47:17,417 --> 00:47:19,042
She said,
"I'll go and come back later."

904
00:47:19,167 --> 00:47:21,500
This is a 90-year-old
ancestral home, right?

905
00:47:21,667 --> 00:47:23,167
All sorts of things can show up here.

906
00:47:23,459 --> 00:47:24,459
Damn!

907
00:47:24,500 --> 00:47:27,626
I've been available right next
door for all these years,

908
00:47:27,709 --> 00:47:30,250
and not a single one
ever came to see me!

909
00:47:30,834 --> 00:47:32,542
Nah, this one seems pretty modern.

910
00:47:33,417 --> 00:47:34,709
She didn't even try to scare me.

911
00:47:35,083 --> 00:47:36,876
She was just sitting there casually,
scrolling through my phone.

912
00:47:38,751 --> 00:47:41,292
Next time you see her,
send her my way.

913
00:47:41,584 --> 00:47:43,000
At least I'll have some company.

914
00:47:45,375 --> 00:47:48,667
Hey, call Paul and ask him
to send an auto rickshaw.

915
00:47:48,751 --> 00:47:50,667
I've got a meeting at ten.

916
00:47:51,500 --> 00:47:52,542
Okay.

917
00:47:57,042 --> 00:47:58,042
Hi!

918
00:47:58,876 --> 00:47:59,876
Good morning.

919
00:47:59,918 --> 00:48:01,292
Please, come in.

920
00:48:02,209 --> 00:48:03,209
Come on in.

921
00:48:03,751 --> 00:48:05,292
Kuttoos had an Android phone, you know.

922
00:48:05,542 --> 00:48:07,584
I was never really
comfortable with Android.

923
00:48:07,834 --> 00:48:10,918
The fact that you have an iPhone
is such a relief, Prabha!

924
00:48:11,584 --> 00:48:12,959
Which 'Kuttoos'?

925
00:48:13,334 --> 00:48:15,042
Remember the puja you did that day?

926
00:48:15,334 --> 00:48:16,417
What was his real name again?

927
00:48:16,542 --> 00:48:17,918
Oh... Avinash!

928
00:48:17,959 --> 00:48:19,709
Gosh, he was such a cutie!

929
00:48:19,918 --> 00:48:21,167
But scared out of his mind.

930
00:48:21,334 --> 00:48:23,125
So scared,
he wouldn't even make eye contact!

931
00:48:23,751 --> 00:48:25,959
How are you supposed to talk to someone
who won't even look at you?

932
00:48:26,542 --> 00:48:27,959
But you're very brave, Prabha.

933
00:48:28,375 --> 00:48:29,542
You have good eye contact.

934
00:48:29,584 --> 00:48:31,083
I like it.
Ten on Ten!

935
00:48:32,083 --> 00:48:33,584
But you did get scared yesterday.

936
00:48:33,626 --> 00:48:35,042
It's totally understandable.

937
00:48:35,083 --> 00:48:36,250
Anyone would have been scared.

938
00:48:36,292 --> 00:48:37,459
It was your first time, right?

939
00:48:38,626 --> 00:48:40,918
By the way, is it okay
if I call you Prabha?

940
00:48:40,959 --> 00:48:41,626
Sure.

941
00:48:41,667 --> 00:48:44,083
I noticed your friends calling
you that in your chats.

942
00:48:45,042 --> 00:48:46,751
Also, it's such an interesting name.

943
00:48:47,292 --> 00:48:48,292
Prabhendu.

944
00:48:48,792 --> 00:48:49,834
Super sweet.

945
00:48:50,209 --> 00:48:51,125
I like it.

946
00:48:51,167 --> 00:48:52,709
- I really like it.
- Indu!

947
00:48:53,125 --> 00:48:54,792
I need the auto rickshaw
only at 11 o'clock.

948
00:48:54,834 --> 00:48:56,250
I just read the notice.

949
00:48:56,959 --> 00:48:57,959
Okay!

950
00:49:02,459 --> 00:49:03,959
Alright, you can have
your phone back now.

951
00:49:04,042 --> 00:49:05,250
I don't need it again till the night.

952
00:49:23,584 --> 00:49:24,626
Anxiety?

953
00:49:27,042 --> 00:49:28,042
Bipolar?

954
00:49:29,250 --> 00:49:30,125
No.

955
00:49:30,167 --> 00:49:31,292
Then what on earth is it?

956
00:49:31,500 --> 00:49:32,500
Huh?!

957
00:49:32,751 --> 00:49:33,751
I was talking to her.

958
00:49:34,042 --> 00:49:35,042
It's not dry yet.

959
00:49:35,542 --> 00:49:36,959
Can you please call Doctor Raphael?

960
00:49:38,292 --> 00:49:39,709
That's me.
What's the matter?

961
00:49:40,042 --> 00:49:41,334
So… I'm a person who performs pujas.

962
00:49:41,375 --> 00:49:43,042
Three days ago,
I went to a house for a puja.

963
00:49:43,083 --> 00:49:44,959
- Not a house, actually a flat, for puja--
- Stop, Stop!

964
00:49:46,083 --> 00:49:47,334
Could you please move, Chechi?

965
00:49:48,626 --> 00:49:50,375
- Continue.
- Like I said, I perform pujas.

966
00:49:50,417 --> 00:49:52,709
Three days ago,
I went to a flat for a puja.

967
00:49:52,834 --> 00:49:54,042
It was meant to drive out a spirit.

968
00:49:54,083 --> 00:49:57,584
His parents said they had
brought him to you, Doctor.

969
00:49:57,834 --> 00:49:59,542
Avinash.
He's slightly chubby…

970
00:49:59,584 --> 00:50:00,542
Oh, yes!

971
00:50:00,584 --> 00:50:02,500
Anyway, after the puja,
he recovered completely.

972
00:50:02,542 --> 00:50:05,626
But now I'm experiencing
the same symptoms he had.

973
00:50:06,167 --> 00:50:08,292
I'm seeing the same girl
he said he used to see.

974
00:50:08,584 --> 00:50:11,667
I saw her last night,
and again today, in broad daylight.

975
00:50:11,876 --> 00:50:13,959
I could hear her voice too.
Crystal clear.

976
00:50:14,083 --> 00:50:15,083
Can you see her right now?

977
00:50:19,167 --> 00:50:20,209
Not right now.

978
00:50:21,125 --> 00:50:22,167
And?

979
00:50:22,417 --> 00:50:23,417
Well, that's all.

980
00:50:23,542 --> 00:50:25,500
Also, the moment I saw that boy,
I understood what the issue was.

981
00:50:25,542 --> 00:50:28,167
Seeing people who aren't there,
hearing voices nobody else hears…

982
00:50:28,209 --> 00:50:29,250
Sheezo-phrenia!

983
00:50:29,292 --> 00:50:30,292
Schizophrenia.

984
00:50:30,334 --> 00:50:32,626
I Googled it
and I have all the symptoms.

985
00:50:33,250 --> 00:50:34,334
- You Googled it?
- Yeah.

986
00:50:34,834 --> 00:50:36,334
I'm willing to take any medication.

987
00:50:36,876 --> 00:50:39,167
Am I talking too fast right now?
Doctor, are you following me so far?

988
00:50:39,709 --> 00:50:41,626
Didn't you say you fixed
Avinash's problem with your puja?

989
00:50:41,667 --> 00:50:42,959
- Yes.
- Then similarly…

990
00:50:43,167 --> 00:50:45,292
why not perform a puja
and cure your own condition?

991
00:50:46,459 --> 00:50:47,500
I...

992
00:50:47,626 --> 00:50:49,209
I don't believe in God, Doctor.

993
00:50:49,250 --> 00:50:50,292
I'm...

994
00:50:50,334 --> 00:50:51,375
an atheist.

995
00:50:51,542 --> 00:50:52,334
Huh?!

996
00:50:52,375 --> 00:50:54,709
Then how can you be doing pujas?

997
00:50:55,792 --> 00:50:57,042
Well...

998
00:50:57,083 --> 00:50:58,751
I'm basically a musician.

999
00:50:58,792 --> 00:51:01,167
A guitarist.
I'm on a short break right now.

1000
00:51:01,417 --> 00:51:03,959
I was trained in all these rituals
until I turned nineteen.

1001
00:51:04,375 --> 00:51:06,292
When did you begin
losing faith in this "item"?

1002
00:51:06,792 --> 00:51:08,083
Which "item," Doctor?

1003
00:51:09,500 --> 00:51:10,500
God.

1004
00:51:13,542 --> 00:51:14,751
Well... that...

1005
00:51:17,959 --> 00:51:19,125
Come with me.

1006
00:51:27,834 --> 00:51:30,500
One day, it was just my mother
and me at home.

1007
00:51:31,375 --> 00:51:34,792
My brother, father, and uncle
had gone to Delhi for a puja.

1008
00:51:36,042 --> 00:51:40,292
Mom and I were watching
an A.R. Rahman concert on Doordarshan.

1009
00:51:41,667 --> 00:51:42,876
Mom had Master's degree in Music.

1010
00:51:42,918 --> 00:51:44,167
She even played the veena.

1011
00:51:46,125 --> 00:51:48,751
We have a shrine inside the house,
almost like a small temple.

1012
00:51:49,792 --> 00:51:51,918
When it was time
to do the puja there,

1013
00:51:51,959 --> 00:51:53,500
I purified myself and went inside.

1014
00:51:53,959 --> 00:51:55,167
We call it the 'Thevaram'.

1015
00:51:56,292 --> 00:51:58,167
Just as I lit the lamp
and began the Puja,

1016
00:51:58,584 --> 00:52:00,083
I heard my mother
calling out to me loudly.

1017
00:52:01,000 --> 00:52:02,167
I ignored it.

1018
00:52:03,292 --> 00:52:04,792
I thought I would
finish the puja first.

1019
00:52:05,334 --> 00:52:06,834
When I went back,

1020
00:52:07,792 --> 00:52:10,375
I saw my mom lying face down
on the floor, next to the sofa.

1021
00:52:11,834 --> 00:52:13,667
The moment I held her,
I knew she was gone.

1022
00:52:14,584 --> 00:52:15,876
It was a cardiac arrest.

1023
00:52:19,751 --> 00:52:21,876
I held my mom in my lap
and stared right at the lamp,

1024
00:52:22,292 --> 00:52:24,209
still burning after the puja.

1025
00:52:25,709 --> 00:52:27,167
I could see it clearly
from where I was.

1026
00:52:28,667 --> 00:52:29,667
That day,

1027
00:52:29,834 --> 00:52:31,626
more than sadness,
what I felt was anger.

1028
00:52:33,542 --> 00:52:34,751
In that moment,

1029
00:52:35,834 --> 00:52:37,626
I lost my connection with God.

1030
00:52:38,083 --> 00:52:39,918
Man, this is your real issue!

1031
00:52:40,751 --> 00:52:42,292
You have deep-seated trauma.

1032
00:52:42,792 --> 00:52:43,792
No way.

1033
00:52:43,834 --> 00:52:45,667
Those two things
have nothing to do with each other.

1034
00:52:45,959 --> 00:52:48,667
Whether they're connected or not,
let's deal with this trauma first.

1035
00:52:49,709 --> 00:52:51,125
What if that girl
shows up again?

1036
00:52:51,417 --> 00:52:52,417
Let her show up.

1037
00:52:52,626 --> 00:52:54,125
She'll go away
the same way she appeared.

1038
00:52:54,375 --> 00:52:55,667
I'll give you a simple fix for that.

1039
00:52:56,250 --> 00:52:58,125
There's a tablet
that contains melatonin.

1040
00:52:58,167 --> 00:52:59,334
It's not a sleeping pill.

1041
00:52:59,667 --> 00:53:01,209
Just take it
before you go to bed.

1042
00:53:01,417 --> 00:53:02,500
You will get a good sleep.

1043
00:53:02,542 --> 00:53:03,500
Huh?

1044
00:53:03,542 --> 00:53:04,959
Don't I need any other medicine?

1045
00:53:05,000 --> 00:53:07,751
There's no better medicine in the world
than a good night's sleep.

1046
00:53:07,918 --> 00:53:09,542
Trust me.
You're fine.

1047
00:53:51,459 --> 00:53:52,459
Okay.

1048
00:53:56,459 --> 00:53:57,542
Okay.

1049
00:54:08,375 --> 00:54:09,375
You are okay!

1050
00:54:14,375 --> 00:54:15,375
You are okay!

1051
00:55:12,584 --> 00:55:13,626
Hi!

1052
00:55:14,375 --> 00:55:17,250
I didn't want to wake you up,
so I just came and sat here quietly.

1053
00:55:17,709 --> 00:55:19,209
Anyway, I'm glad
I saw you today.

1054
00:55:19,250 --> 00:55:21,292
Why should we keep
startling each other like this?

1055
00:55:21,459 --> 00:55:22,959
We're well past that stage now,
aren't we?

1056
00:55:27,042 --> 00:55:28,209
Whoa! Relax.

1057
00:55:28,584 --> 00:55:30,042
This isn't a dream.

1058
00:55:30,709 --> 00:55:32,375
Look, the time is 1:40 AM.

1059
00:55:32,459 --> 00:55:34,667
Uncle just went to the wash room
and got back in bed.

1060
00:55:34,709 --> 00:55:36,334
As usual, he didn't flush.

1061
00:55:36,459 --> 00:55:37,542
Shall I flush it for him?

1062
00:55:37,584 --> 00:55:38,626
I can do it from here.

1063
00:55:46,042 --> 00:55:47,292
Shall I turn on the light?

1064
00:55:50,417 --> 00:55:52,542
Sorry, I'm just figuring this out.

1065
00:55:53,209 --> 00:55:54,584
You just need to change the bulb.

1066
00:55:54,918 --> 00:55:55,918
Indu!

1067
00:55:58,083 --> 00:55:59,334
I think he got up.

1068
00:55:59,792 --> 00:56:01,709
Tell you what.
You go back to sleep.

1069
00:56:02,000 --> 00:56:03,167
You've taken the medicine, right?

1070
00:56:03,375 --> 00:56:06,250
And if you don't mind,
I need to check some stuff on this.

1071
00:56:06,375 --> 00:56:07,667
I'll return it in the morning.

1072
00:56:12,250 --> 00:56:13,918
What was that sound?

1073
00:56:16,375 --> 00:56:18,000
Oh! He can't see me.

1074
00:56:19,626 --> 00:56:20,876
Your uncle can't see me.

1075
00:56:21,250 --> 00:56:22,250
Oh!

1076
00:56:22,542 --> 00:56:23,542
What do you mean, 'Oh'?

1077
00:56:23,918 --> 00:56:25,292
I asked what that sound was.

1078
00:56:25,417 --> 00:56:26,417
Oh, that...

1079
00:56:26,876 --> 00:56:28,709
I think the bulb blew
from a voltage surge.

1080
00:56:28,751 --> 00:56:29,918
My dear Indu,

1081
00:56:29,959 --> 00:56:31,959
just say your prayers
and go to sleep.

1082
00:56:32,125 --> 00:56:35,083
No faith in God,
but scared out of your wits!

1083
00:56:35,500 --> 00:56:36,500
Ugh!

1084
00:56:42,542 --> 00:56:43,542
Go back to sleep, Prabha.

1085
00:56:43,792 --> 00:56:45,000
I'm okay out here.

1086
00:56:45,083 --> 00:56:48,500
By the way, good call on placing
the return request for the kurta.

1087
00:56:48,542 --> 00:56:50,375
I ordered the white kurta
with lavender accents.

1088
00:56:50,417 --> 00:56:52,542
But I think they sent
white with pink instead.

1089
00:56:52,918 --> 00:56:55,959
Anyway, I've scheduled
the pickup for tomorrow.

1090
00:56:56,125 --> 00:56:57,375
Just make sure
you hand it over.

1091
00:57:04,959 --> 00:57:06,500
Is there something
you want to ask me?

1092
00:57:10,125 --> 00:57:11,500
Finally!
Go on, ask me.

1093
00:57:14,000 --> 00:57:15,000
Who... are you?

1094
00:57:20,209 --> 00:57:21,667
I hate to say this.

1095
00:57:23,125 --> 00:57:25,083
But I think I'm a ghost.

1096
00:57:26,083 --> 00:57:28,375
Yeah, I think so.

1097
00:57:50,375 --> 00:57:51,167
Pradeep...

1098
00:57:51,209 --> 00:57:53,375
July 12th and 13th
are auspicious days.

1099
00:57:53,667 --> 00:57:54,667
Plan it accordingly.

1100
00:57:54,792 --> 00:57:55,792
Okay?

1101
00:57:57,167 --> 00:57:58,542
What are you doing here
at this hour?

1102
00:58:00,292 --> 00:58:01,417
What's in the bag?

1103
00:58:04,542 --> 00:58:05,751
Psst... psst!

1104
00:58:05,918 --> 00:58:07,667
Don't! Don't!
[chants slokas]

1105
00:58:07,709 --> 00:58:08,918
Psst... psst!
Over here!

1106
00:58:10,417 --> 00:58:11,417
Where did you see it?

1107
00:58:11,542 --> 00:58:12,626
In my room.

1108
00:58:12,918 --> 00:58:14,042
- It's still here.
- Still there?

1109
00:58:14,083 --> 00:58:15,542
Why didn't you tell me
this when you called?

1110
00:58:15,709 --> 00:58:17,459
- But my phone is with her!
- Oh.

1111
00:58:17,500 --> 00:58:18,500
Come on.

1112
00:58:19,876 --> 00:58:21,083
Will she hurt me?

1113
00:58:22,667 --> 00:58:24,500
- I don't think so.
- You don't "think" so?

1114
00:58:25,209 --> 00:58:26,542
Why is this door locked?

1115
00:58:26,918 --> 00:58:28,500
So she can't get out.

1116
00:58:28,709 --> 00:58:29,709
Oh.

1117
00:58:29,876 --> 00:58:30,918
The ghost? Seriously?

1118
00:58:32,250 --> 00:58:33,417
Open it.

1119
00:58:36,959 --> 00:58:38,459
And that?
Open that too!

1120
00:58:40,792 --> 00:58:41,834
She's gone!

1121
00:58:43,167 --> 00:58:44,751
Didn't I tell you, Indu?

1122
00:58:45,000 --> 00:58:46,834
It's just your mind playing tricks.

1123
00:58:47,876 --> 00:58:51,125
The rest will sort itself
out after the puja.

1124
00:58:51,167 --> 00:58:52,375
You know who's doing it, right?

1125
00:58:53,834 --> 00:58:55,083
East should be this side, right?

1126
00:58:56,250 --> 00:58:57,375
- That side.
- Right.

1127
00:58:58,751 --> 00:59:00,292
No, I'll handle this.

1128
00:59:00,334 --> 00:59:01,292
Right now, you're the client.

1129
00:59:01,334 --> 00:59:02,417
- You've got a lamp?
- Yes.

1130
00:59:02,459 --> 00:59:03,751
Bring it here.
I need to light it.

1131
00:59:03,792 --> 00:59:04,792
I'll handle that as well.

1132
00:59:06,375 --> 00:59:08,751
Once you conquer fear,
the battle is half-won...

1133
00:59:08,792 --> 00:59:10,459
Hey! Where are you off to?

1134
00:59:11,125 --> 00:59:12,167
You asked me to bring the lamp.

1135
00:59:12,209 --> 00:59:13,667
Don't go alone.
I'll come with you.

1136
00:59:20,751 --> 00:59:23,000
Oil, coconut, matches…
Take everything at once.

1137
00:59:23,042 --> 00:59:25,000
Don't keep going in and
out while I'm inside.

1138
00:59:25,042 --> 00:59:26,083
It isn't safe.

1139
00:59:26,125 --> 00:59:27,626
What are you staring at?
Let's go!

1140
00:59:29,209 --> 00:59:30,751
My god, I've never
seen anyone so scared!

1141
00:59:33,542 --> 00:59:34,626
Phew! Safe!

1142
00:59:40,626 --> 00:59:43,417
Uncle, I've come to collect
a parcel for return.

1143
00:59:43,709 --> 00:59:44,792
What parcel?

1144
00:59:44,959 --> 00:59:46,167
It's a kurta set.

1145
00:59:47,042 --> 00:59:48,500
But nobody in this
house wears kurtas.

1146
00:59:48,542 --> 00:59:49,959
This one is a ladies' kurta.

1147
00:59:50,000 --> 00:59:52,083
Prabhendu must be your son, right?

1148
00:59:52,459 --> 00:59:54,167
- Yes.
- Ah, he ordered it.

1149
00:59:55,375 --> 00:59:56,459
- Here you go.
- Right!

1150
00:59:57,167 --> 00:59:58,626
Indutty gave it to
me in the morning.

1151
00:59:59,918 --> 01:00:01,709
Valentine's Day is
around the corner, right?

1152
01:00:01,751 --> 01:00:03,334
Must be a gift for someone special.

1153
01:00:03,459 --> 01:00:04,792
Oh dear, this Indutty!

1154
01:00:13,834 --> 01:00:14,834
Phew!

1155
01:00:15,250 --> 01:00:16,876
I'm not just saying this
because I did it...

1156
01:00:16,918 --> 01:00:18,626
- What?
- The puja was a big success.

1157
01:00:18,709 --> 01:00:19,709
Hmm.

1158
01:00:20,000 --> 01:00:21,375
That thing you spoke about…

1159
01:00:21,459 --> 01:00:22,459
She's a real terror.

1160
01:00:22,667 --> 01:00:24,375
I watched her leave
with my own eyes!

1161
01:00:26,083 --> 01:00:27,083
Hmm.

1162
01:00:28,042 --> 01:00:30,167
I'm thinking maybe
I should see that doctor again.

1163
01:00:30,209 --> 01:00:31,375
Come on!
What for?

1164
01:00:31,417 --> 01:00:32,626
This is a form of treatment too.

1165
01:00:32,667 --> 01:00:35,626
This time, I decided to add
a touch of extra sorcery,

1166
01:00:35,751 --> 01:00:36,751
just for flavour.

1167
01:00:36,792 --> 01:00:37,792
And it worked perfectly.

1168
01:00:39,709 --> 01:00:40,751
Why do you look so unconvinced?

1169
01:00:40,792 --> 01:00:42,083
No, I'm not doubting anything.

1170
01:00:42,125 --> 01:00:43,626
Alright then! Get up.

1171
01:00:43,959 --> 01:00:44,959
Oh my...

1172
01:00:45,125 --> 01:00:46,918
Let me know once you're
done being scared.

1173
01:00:47,667 --> 01:00:49,209
There are a few pending pujas.

1174
01:00:49,250 --> 01:00:50,500
Let's wrap those up too.

1175
01:00:51,167 --> 01:00:52,250
Alright then, I'll get going.

1176
01:00:52,500 --> 01:00:53,751
- Okay.
- I forgot something.

1177
01:00:53,834 --> 01:00:56,542
Your father is upset that you
don't visit the temple anymore.

1178
01:00:56,834 --> 01:00:57,959
At least go once in a while.

1179
01:00:58,042 --> 01:00:59,000
Poor soul.

1180
01:00:59,042 --> 01:01:00,042
What are you thinking?

1181
01:01:00,375 --> 01:01:01,292
That item?

1182
01:01:01,334 --> 01:01:02,417
She's gone!

1183
01:01:02,500 --> 01:01:03,959
Chill! Okay?

1184
01:01:04,584 --> 01:01:06,417
Let me see how she
dares to return now!

1185
01:01:06,584 --> 01:01:07,584
Okay.

1186
01:01:09,584 --> 01:01:10,500
Huh!

1187
01:01:10,542 --> 01:01:11,626
Done getting shocked?

1188
01:01:14,292 --> 01:01:15,292
Who's he calling an "item"?

1189
01:01:15,334 --> 01:01:16,334
Do I look like an item?

1190
01:01:32,292 --> 01:01:33,667
Don't go without talking to me.

1191
01:01:33,751 --> 01:01:35,834
If you keep running away,
that's all you'll ever do.

1192
01:01:37,042 --> 01:01:40,500
Listen... have I done anything to you
like those horror-movie ghosts?

1193
01:01:42,834 --> 01:01:43,834
Yes or no?

1194
01:01:45,417 --> 01:01:46,417
No.

1195
01:01:46,542 --> 01:01:48,250
Other than you getting
shocked seeing me

1196
01:01:48,292 --> 01:01:49,709
and me getting shocked
seeing you,

1197
01:01:49,751 --> 01:01:51,459
have I troubled you in any way?

1198
01:01:53,667 --> 01:01:54,667
Yes or no?

1199
01:01:56,209 --> 01:01:57,250
No.

1200
01:01:57,626 --> 01:01:59,959
Look, I don't have
clarity on this either.

1201
01:02:00,083 --> 01:02:01,667
I don't even know what happened to me.

1202
01:02:01,709 --> 01:02:04,250
And... I have no clue
why I'm following you around

1203
01:02:04,292 --> 01:02:06,083
as if we're connected
via Bluetooth.

1204
01:02:06,209 --> 01:02:07,751
Do you even realise
how hard this is for me?

1205
01:02:11,042 --> 01:02:12,042
Huh?

1206
01:02:13,334 --> 01:02:14,334
It's just that...

1207
01:02:15,000 --> 01:02:16,167
you didn't ask yes or no.

1208
01:02:16,959 --> 01:02:19,083
For the love of Jesus,
don't be scared of me!

1209
01:02:19,334 --> 01:02:20,709
It makes me feel guilty
for no reason.

1210
01:02:21,542 --> 01:02:22,542
Jesus?

1211
01:02:23,334 --> 01:02:24,334
Huh?

1212
01:02:26,500 --> 01:02:27,792
So, you're a Christian?

1213
01:02:28,709 --> 01:02:29,792
Oh! Yeah.

1214
01:02:34,167 --> 01:02:35,250
No wonder!

1215
01:03:16,918 --> 01:03:18,000
Do you sell crosses here?

1216
01:03:19,083 --> 01:03:20,083
What's the purpose?

1217
01:03:21,250 --> 01:03:22,292
For...

1218
01:03:22,500 --> 01:03:23,542
protection.

1219
01:03:23,584 --> 01:03:24,751
Protection from what?

1220
01:03:25,876 --> 01:03:27,292
No, no… just general safety.

1221
01:03:27,542 --> 01:03:28,709
Safety from what exactly?

1222
01:03:28,751 --> 01:03:30,667
For my own peace of mind, Chetta.

1223
01:03:31,292 --> 01:03:32,292
Wood or metal?

1224
01:03:33,334 --> 01:03:34,667
Which one is more powerful?

1225
01:03:34,876 --> 01:03:37,000
This isn't a light bulb
you pick by wattage.

1226
01:03:37,709 --> 01:03:39,250
That depends on your faith.

1227
01:03:39,584 --> 01:03:40,584
Lali!

1228
01:03:40,667 --> 01:03:41,709
Yes?

1229
01:03:42,250 --> 01:03:43,542
Show him the crosses.

1230
01:03:45,250 --> 01:03:46,542
Are you Roman Catholic?

1231
01:03:48,250 --> 01:03:49,250
No.

1232
01:03:49,375 --> 01:03:50,792
Oh, from the Jacobite Church then.

1233
01:03:52,542 --> 01:03:53,876
Err...

1234
01:03:54,000 --> 01:03:55,000
No.

1235
01:03:57,542 --> 01:03:58,792
Mar Thoma church, then?

1236
01:04:00,125 --> 01:04:01,250
Mar...

1237
01:04:01,959 --> 01:04:02,959
Yes.

1238
01:04:04,626 --> 01:04:06,250
- Huh?
- Yes, you're right.

1239
01:04:06,292 --> 01:04:07,709
Ah, I knew it!

1240
01:04:07,751 --> 01:04:09,500
The moment I saw you,

1241
01:04:09,542 --> 01:04:11,584
I knew you were
a proper Mar Thoma boy.

1242
01:04:11,876 --> 01:04:13,167
- Yes.
- Right.

1243
01:04:13,209 --> 01:04:15,334
So, pick whichever one
you like. Okay?

1244
01:04:25,042 --> 01:04:30,542
[chants slokas]

1245
01:04:40,667 --> 01:04:42,083
So, this should clear things up, right?

1246
01:04:44,584 --> 01:04:47,000
I mean, I'm literally standing
surrounded by crosses right now.

1247
01:04:47,083 --> 01:04:48,083
Including you.

1248
01:04:49,876 --> 01:04:51,584
Hey! If Jesus had a problem with me,

1249
01:04:51,626 --> 01:04:53,500
wouldn't I be gone by now?

1250
01:04:56,042 --> 01:04:57,918
Look, I honestly don't know
how I became a ghost,

1251
01:04:57,959 --> 01:05:02,167
or why I am one,
or how to stop being one.

1252
01:05:02,542 --> 01:05:03,918
And you know
what's the funny part?

1253
01:05:04,000 --> 01:05:06,250
I can't remember
a single important detail!

1254
01:05:06,584 --> 01:05:08,083
I can't even recall my name!

1255
01:05:13,000 --> 01:05:14,000
Answer it.

1256
01:05:18,375 --> 01:05:20,083
- Faizal...
- Hey, Prabha...

1257
01:05:20,125 --> 01:05:22,876
Wherever you are, drop everything
and get to the studio by midnight.

1258
01:05:22,918 --> 01:05:24,626
Viraj sir said he'll
join on a video call.

1259
01:05:24,667 --> 01:05:27,083
He wants to test you
for a track in his next film.

1260
01:05:27,250 --> 01:05:28,584
I'm kind of stuck right now.

1261
01:05:29,209 --> 01:05:30,626
Can we reschedule?

1262
01:05:30,792 --> 01:05:33,500
Don't be an idiot, Prabha!

1263
01:05:33,876 --> 01:05:35,709
If you miss this now,
there won't be another chance.

1264
01:05:35,751 --> 01:05:38,250
I've given Saadhya my word.
Stop stalling and get here.

1265
01:05:38,292 --> 01:05:39,375
It's 5:00 PM already.

1266
01:05:39,626 --> 01:05:40,626
- I'll be there.
- Okay.

1267
01:05:45,792 --> 01:05:46,792
I heard that.

1268
01:05:47,250 --> 01:05:48,250
Congrats.

1269
01:06:25,626 --> 01:06:27,250
Ah! Come in, come in.

1270
01:06:30,167 --> 01:06:32,334
I didn't take the bike,
in case it rained tonight.

1271
01:06:32,459 --> 01:06:34,417
Caught a direct bus.
It was pretty comfortable.

1272
01:06:34,834 --> 01:06:36,626
You don't mind me
eating non-veg, do you?

1273
01:06:37,042 --> 01:06:38,042
Not at all.

1274
01:06:38,167 --> 01:06:39,751
I think I'll order a dosa.

1275
01:06:39,876 --> 01:06:41,125
I'll order for you, man.

1276
01:06:41,167 --> 01:06:42,167
You haven't eaten yet?

1277
01:06:43,250 --> 01:06:44,542
How about podi masala dosa?

1278
01:06:45,834 --> 01:06:46,834
Yeah.

1279
01:06:46,876 --> 01:06:48,209
Who are you looking for?

1280
01:06:48,626 --> 01:06:49,626
Oh, nothing.

1281
01:06:49,876 --> 01:06:51,626
I asked if podi masala dosa is okay.

1282
01:06:51,667 --> 01:06:52,667
Yeah, that's fine.

1283
01:06:54,292 --> 01:06:56,584
Dude, hold on.
Saadhya's calling.

1284
01:06:57,167 --> 01:06:58,459
Hello, Saadhya...

1285
01:06:59,792 --> 01:07:00,792
Yeah.

1286
01:07:00,834 --> 01:07:02,042
He's logged in already?

1287
01:07:02,083 --> 01:07:03,500
No, no problem.
We're coming.

1288
01:07:03,584 --> 01:07:05,876
Dude, Viraj sir has already logged in.

1289
01:07:05,918 --> 01:07:07,083
Come on, hurry up!

1290
01:07:07,167 --> 01:07:08,167
What about my dosa?

1291
01:07:08,417 --> 01:07:10,792
I'm ditching my biriyani, and you're
worried about your dosa? Move!

1292
01:07:27,083 --> 01:07:28,167
Prabha, ready.

1293
01:07:28,250 --> 01:07:29,375
He's here.

1294
01:07:29,417 --> 01:07:30,876
Hi Faizal. All good?

1295
01:07:31,000 --> 01:07:32,959
Hi, sir. All good, sir.
All good.

1296
01:07:33,209 --> 01:07:36,083
The guitarist. Is he ready?
What's his name?

1297
01:07:36,459 --> 01:07:38,459
Prabhendu, sir.
Prabhendu.

1298
01:07:38,500 --> 01:07:39,584
Shall I call him here, sir?

1299
01:07:39,626 --> 01:07:40,834
No, no. No need.

1300
01:07:40,876 --> 01:07:42,334
I can hear what he plays, right?

1301
01:07:42,459 --> 01:07:43,459
Yeah, of course. Of course.

1302
01:07:43,500 --> 01:07:44,792
Okay then.
Let's start now.

1303
01:07:46,500 --> 01:07:47,542
Hey...

1304
01:07:47,667 --> 01:07:49,042
Sir has composed a new track.

1305
01:07:49,083 --> 01:07:50,209
He needs a guitar groove for it.

1306
01:07:50,626 --> 01:07:51,626
Kill it!

1307
01:08:24,083 --> 01:08:26,334
Faizal, I need a catchy
riff for the melody.

1308
01:08:26,375 --> 01:08:27,375
Yes, sir. Yes, sir.

1309
01:08:28,250 --> 01:08:29,417
Prabha... 2-bar cue.

1310
01:08:29,792 --> 01:08:30,792
Yeah, okay.

1311
01:08:40,500 --> 01:08:41,834
No, no.
Stop, stop.

1312
01:08:41,876 --> 01:08:44,083
Prabhendu, I don't want that.

1313
01:08:44,209 --> 01:08:47,000
It's not sounding good.
Try some strumming.

1314
01:08:49,834 --> 01:08:51,417
Prabha, don't try anything
too fancy.

1315
01:08:51,459 --> 01:08:52,751
Just stick to your comfort zone.

1316
01:08:52,792 --> 01:08:53,834
Okay.

1317
01:09:09,000 --> 01:09:10,167
No, no, no.

1318
01:09:10,334 --> 01:09:11,792
What are you doing, man?

1319
01:09:11,918 --> 01:09:14,334
Feel the melody and try again.

1320
01:09:15,959 --> 01:09:17,417
Faizal, give him a shorter cue.

1321
01:09:17,500 --> 01:09:18,500
Sure. Sure, sir.

1322
01:09:19,334 --> 01:09:20,834
Prabha, what's wrong with you?

1323
01:09:21,250 --> 01:09:22,500
Let's go. Ready.

1324
01:09:23,083 --> 01:09:24,292
Okay.

1325
01:09:24,751 --> 01:09:25,751
Take.

1326
01:09:32,500 --> 01:09:33,584
Stop, stop, stop.

1327
01:09:33,709 --> 01:09:35,250
This is not even close!

1328
01:09:35,542 --> 01:09:36,918
Faizal, what is this?

1329
01:09:36,959 --> 01:09:38,834
I already have people in Mumbai
who play like this.

1330
01:09:39,083 --> 01:09:40,500
I want that magic!

1331
01:09:40,542 --> 01:09:43,209
We shouldn't waste our time.
Let's look for someone else.

1332
01:09:43,292 --> 01:09:44,584
He just can't do it.

1333
01:09:51,918 --> 01:09:53,375
Just follow the melody.

1334
01:09:56,250 --> 01:09:57,292
Huh?!

1335
01:10:00,500 --> 01:10:01,542
What is it, man?

1336
01:10:02,334 --> 01:10:03,500
Oh, it's nothing.

1337
01:10:04,459 --> 01:10:05,918
Prabha, focus only on the melody.

1338
01:10:06,083 --> 01:10:07,125
It's that simple.

1339
01:10:15,667 --> 01:10:16,667
Play this.

1340
01:10:19,417 --> 01:10:20,417
Prabha...

1341
01:10:20,959 --> 01:10:21,959
What do I do?

1342
01:10:23,792 --> 01:10:25,209
- Ready.
- Okay, man.

1343
01:10:25,709 --> 01:10:27,334
Sir... One last time, sir?

1344
01:10:27,959 --> 01:10:29,500
Okay, try.

1345
01:10:29,667 --> 01:10:31,167
Okay, sir.
Thank you, thank you.

1346
01:10:31,209 --> 01:10:32,250
Prabha, take.

1347
01:10:54,667 --> 01:10:56,250
Oh, nice!
I like it!

1348
01:10:56,459 --> 01:10:58,751
Faizal, this is exactly what I want!

1349
01:10:58,834 --> 01:10:59,834
Thank you, sir.

1350
01:10:59,876 --> 01:11:01,584
Prabha, that's brilliant.
Stick with that.

1351
01:11:03,792 --> 01:11:05,083
Super. Add one more layer.

1352
01:11:08,500 --> 01:11:10,459
Faizal, turn up the reverb.

1353
01:11:10,500 --> 01:11:11,500
I'll add one more layer.

1354
01:11:11,542 --> 01:11:12,626
Ready!

1355
01:11:21,667 --> 01:11:22,667
Too good, man!

1356
01:11:23,417 --> 01:11:24,417
Continue!

1357
01:11:42,417 --> 01:11:43,209
Too good!

1358
01:11:43,250 --> 01:11:45,292
Faizal, call him!
I want to see him.

1359
01:11:45,751 --> 01:11:46,751
Sure, sir.

1360
01:11:46,959 --> 01:11:48,334
Prabha, come over here.

1361
01:11:48,417 --> 01:11:49,459
Sir wants to see you.

1362
01:11:57,834 --> 01:11:59,209
You killed it, man!

1363
01:12:00,292 --> 01:12:02,167
You just made the tune better,
Prabhendu.

1364
01:12:02,375 --> 01:12:04,334
We will do the full song together
in Mumbai.

1365
01:12:04,375 --> 01:12:05,417
Thank you, sir.

1366
01:12:05,542 --> 01:12:06,500
Perfect!

1367
01:12:06,542 --> 01:12:08,375
Faizal, I'll ask Saadhya to coordinate.

1368
01:12:08,417 --> 01:12:09,417
Okay.

1369
01:12:48,209 --> 01:12:49,751
Your destination is on the left.

1370
01:12:52,751 --> 01:12:53,876
Hey! Kiddo!

1371
01:13:04,542 --> 01:13:05,542
Hey, look at that.

1372
01:13:06,709 --> 01:13:08,626
To be honest,
I didn't quite get that initially.

1373
01:13:10,042 --> 01:13:11,042
Great!

1374
01:13:12,626 --> 01:13:13,667
And then?

1375
01:13:13,751 --> 01:13:15,375
That's exactly what I was thinking.

1376
01:13:15,667 --> 01:13:18,292
I know music, and I know
how guitar chords work.

1377
01:13:19,375 --> 01:13:20,375
Oh Jesus!

1378
01:13:20,500 --> 01:13:22,000
Kuttoos was a guitarist too!

1379
01:13:22,500 --> 01:13:24,042
Music connects the three of us!

1380
01:13:26,209 --> 01:13:27,209
Strange!

1381
01:13:27,751 --> 01:13:29,042
Also, you're an acoustic guy?

1382
01:13:29,959 --> 01:13:31,542
Electric Guitar is my favourite.

1383
01:13:31,959 --> 01:13:33,792
But people like Viraj sir

1384
01:13:34,083 --> 01:13:36,918
usually prefer acoustic
when they're composing.

1385
01:13:36,959 --> 01:13:38,792
Ah, I see.

1386
01:13:40,375 --> 01:13:42,167
Looks like you've lost your
fear and found some guts.

1387
01:13:43,292 --> 01:13:44,334
The fear is gone,

1388
01:13:44,751 --> 01:13:46,042
but the confusion remains.

1389
01:13:46,542 --> 01:13:47,751
Just relax, Prabha.

1390
01:13:47,792 --> 01:13:49,292
I think I'm just delulu.

1391
01:13:49,959 --> 01:13:52,042
Alright. So, delulu...
Ordering things online--

